title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Boil peppers for 5 minutes.
Brown ground meat.
Add chopped onion, garlic salt, flour, milk, fresh tomatoes, tomato sauce, cooked rice, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and stuff into peppers.
Cook at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: betty's brisket
directions: Will also need a large size brown and bake bag.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onion in butter.
Add cheese and melt.
Add milk and mayo; mix well.
Add chicken and broccoli; mix well and cook for 10 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Roll out croissant and slice into long strips.
Place strips on mixture in a lattice pattern.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a hot oven for about 5 minutes. Reduce temperature to about 350° and bake about 1 hour.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Blend together butter, sugar and eggs.
Gradually add flour, mixing thoroughly, then add vanilla.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool in pan for 2 hours, then rack cool.

title: red cabbage
directions: Melt Crisco.
Cook cut up cabbage.
Add salt.
Add vinegar. Slow cook for 1 hour.
Add jelly, sugar and apples; stir.
Cook for another hour.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar.
When cool, pour over vegetables and let marinate several hours before serving.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together and your salad is made! Refrigerate and serve when chilled.

title: curried chicken divine
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Remove from bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli in broth from chicken.
Place broccoli in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, evaporated milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Top with buttered, toasted bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corny dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except wieners, and let stand 1 hour. Dip wieners in batter and deep fry until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Stir chocolate into water over low heat until melted; cool. Beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth; add chocolate.
Spoon mixture into pie crust; chill for 3 hours.

title: my brother-in-law cornelius mccarthy's scones
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well, then add buttermilk to form round ball for kneading.
On floured surface, knead to form loaf for about 10 minutes.
When formed, turn into greased pan or Turk's head.
Place into 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.
Test for doneness with piece of spaghetti.
Cool for 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: meat ball casserole
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, milk and seasonings. Shape into meat balls. Brown and cook 10 minutes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until golden.
Slowly add can of cannelini beans and stir.
Add parsley, oregano, basil and salt. Add 1 can of water to beans; stir and add tomato paste.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.
In a 3-quart pot, boil water for pasta.
Cook according to package directions.
Drain and add beans. Heat through; stir and top with Romano cheese.

title: orange lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and set aside.
Be sure to save the grease.
Break lettuce into bite size pieces.
Add oranges (drained).
Toast pecans for 3 to 5 minutes at 350° (careful, they burn easily).
Add pecans to salad and stir.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Then add bacon pieces.

title: fluffy seven minute frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except the vanilla in the top part of a double boiler and continuously beat with an electric mixer or egg beater until light and fluffy.
Add the vanilla.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a medium size bowl. Blend in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Add cheese, cayenne pepper and water.
Mix well until mixture holds together.
Roll out and cut into strips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, boil milk and sugar for about 3 minutes. Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter and mix well. Quickly pour in a buttered 8-inch pan. Chill in ice box until set. Cut into small squares.

title: beef barbecue for 3 dozen rolls
directions: Chop pepper, onions and celery fine; steam until tender (don't use much water to steam this).
Add tomato soup, catsup and chili sauce to it.
Add pepper, salt and a little chili powder to taste. Crumble the ground beef in it.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes. Great for picnics and when serving a lot of people.

title: herb jenneskens' beef tenderloin in marchand sauce
directions: Roast beef in a 400° oven for 35 minutes or to desired doneness.
While tenderloin is roasting, prepare sauce.
Cook shallots and wine in saucepan until reduced to 1/4 original volume.
Cool slightly.
Cream butter with parsley, salt and pepper.
Blend into wine mixture.
Slice beef into 1/2-inch thick slices and serve with sauce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: easy caramel coffee cake
directions: Mix nuts, sugar and margarine.
Cut up 1 can of biscuits into quarters.
Put in the bottom of a greased Bundt pan.
Pour 1/2 of butter, sugar and nuts over biscuits.
Cut up 2nd can of biscuits and put on top of mixture (layering).
Pour rest of ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When done, flip onto plate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Thaw frozen peas.
Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onion into bite size pieces.
Add peas if desired.
Mix ingredients together.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add to other ingredients.
Spread cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: do ahead party mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes and boil in salted water.
Drain well; mash until smooth.
Mix cream cheese with sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Beat into potatoes and whip until smooth and fluffy.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole; dot with butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Tastes best if refrigerated 12 to 24 hours before baking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon-cheese cake
directions: Cream
the
butter
and
sugar really good; sift flour, salt and
baking
powder together 3 times.
Add flour and milk alternately,
beating
good
after	each one.
Add flavorings. Beat egg whites until fluffy and fold in cake mixture.
Grease three 9
1/2-inch
cake
pans and line bottoms with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar, beet juice, vinegar, horseradish and sour cream.
Stir until smooth.
Add beets and chill.

title: vanilla sheath cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and shortening to a boil. Pour over dry ingredients. Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked lasagne with meat and cream sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 12 x 3-inch casserole.
Cook the lasagne and drain on paper towel. Combine first 4 items and chop
to very small pieces.
Melt butter in skillet. Add veggies.
Cook until lightly browned, then transfer to saucepan.
Heat oil and cook meats.
Add wine to meats; increase heat to boil.
Cook until liquid (broth) is gone and add to veggies.
Cook livers in butter 3 to 4 minutes until firm and light brown.
Dice and add to sauce 10 minutes before done.
Add seasoning.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Heat milk and soup.
Take off fire and add onions, cheese and beef.
Cream well.
Add to noodles and mix well.

title: easiest bars ever
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
In large bowl, mix cake mix, margarine, eggs and nuts by hand.
Spread in pan and bake 15 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: quick taco salad
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Remove from skillet; set aside. In same skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed.
Stir in meat mixture, salsa and chili powder; cook 3 to 4 more minutes. Arrange lettuce on platter, top with rice mixture, tomato, cheese and tortilla chips.

title: island chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together jam, salad dressing and soup mix.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Cover with 2 cups of water.
Pour jam mixture over top of chicken.
Bake chicken for 2 hours, turning after 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Top with French onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cocoa icing
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add all, except cream and vanilla, and mix.
Then add cream and beat until consistency to spread.
Add vanilla.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Heat butter with soup and blend in sour cream. Add onion and cheese to soup mixture.
Stir in drained potatoes. Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle buttered croutons over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken, cool and bone.
Place in casserole dish.
Chop onion and pepper, spread over chicken.
Spread layer of cheese over chicken, then a layer of Doritos chips.
In mixing bowl mix both cans of soup, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Spread over mixture in dish, top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mini meat pies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except pie crust mix; mix well.
Prepare pie crust mix as directed.
Divide dough in half.
On floured surface, roll out half the dough to 10 x 13-inch rectangle, 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 20 (2 1/2-inch) squares.
Spoon 1 heaping teaspoonful meat mixture in center of each square; fold as desired.
Repeat with remaining dough and meat mixture.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chili rellenos
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half of chiles and half of cheese. Repeat, but save 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add flour and milk; beat until blended.
Pour over chiles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and knead together and let raise for 10 minutes, then spread out on cookie sheet or pizza pie pans.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook to hard ball stage, stirring constantly.
Combine beaten egg whites and gelatin; beat until mixture forms peaks.
Pour hot syrup in thin stream into egg whites, beating until candy loses gloss and holds shape.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: creamy corn
directions: In saucepan, combine cream cheese, milk, butter and onion salt.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Add corn and heat.

title: patty's monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 parts.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in bag; add biscuits and shake.
Drop into greased tube pan.
Melt butter or margarine and add brown sugar; stir.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 400° until done, approximately 20 minutes.
When done, turn pan over on plate.
Don't cut or slice, just pick off and eat.

title: ham balls
directions: Blend ham, beef and pork.
Add all other ingredients.
Form meat balls and place in baking pan.

title: bonnie's broccoli chicken bake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, place broccoli spears to cover bottom.
Place 6 boneless chicken breasts on top of broccoli.
Mix cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup together and pour over top of chicken and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, top with can of Durkee's French fried onions and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Drain the cooked broccoli and put on bottom of greased casserole.
Add chicken.
Mix the soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Pour over the chicken.
Mix the bread crumbs with the melted oleo.
Pour over the soup.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: magic white frosting
directions: Mix in saucepan, sugar, salt, cream of tartar and water. Stir.
Bring to a full boil.
Place two egg whites in small mixer bowl.
Do not beat until syrup is cooked.
Pour syrup slowly over the egg whites, while beating at high speed, until all syrup has been added.
Reduce speed to medium.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture is of spreading consistency.
Ice cake.
May sprinkle on coconut, if desired.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole dish.
Mix flour and sugar; blend into margarine and warm water.
Pour fruit on top.
Don't mix; dough rises to top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and glazed on top.
(Fruit may be fresh, canned or pie filling mix.)

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Spread 1/2 crushed cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: In a bowl, blend together mashed bananas, brown sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix oats, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine oat mixture with banana mixture; fold in mixed dried fruit, raisins and/or chocolate chips, if desired.
Drop cookies by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 42 cookies.

title: crock-pot roast with gravy
directions: Place roast with 1 tablespoon water in the crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 hours.
Add soups.
Do not add water.
Continue cooking on low for 6 more hours.
Meat should be tender.
Serves 6.

title: mango shake
directions: First, slice mangos in cubes and place in a blender.
Then, add 2 cups of milk and add sugar.
Lastly, put in 7 (or more) cubes of ice and blend well.
Pour in glass and enjoy!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken fricassee cuban style
directions: Place chicken parts in a large deep skillet.
Add m.s.g., garlic, onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, bay leaves, cumin, oregano, raisins, olives and vinegar.
Cover and bring to a boil. Turn heat down and simmer 1 hour, turning chicken occasionally. Remove chicken to a platter and serve the sauce over rice or noodles.

title: meatball sub casserole
directions: Combine onions, crumbs, Parmesan and beef.
Make 1-inch balls, bake on rack in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until done.
Arrange bread in single layer in ungreased 13 x 9 pan.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, Italian seasoning and pepper, spread on bread, sprinkle with 1/2 c. mozzarella.
Combine meatballs, sauce, water and garlic, pour over bread and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with rest of mozzarella.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
This is easier to eat than a meatball sub!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion, nuts and 3/4 cup cheese as for a salad.
Blend chicken soup with mayonnaise.
Mix "salad" with soup mixture and put into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with dry Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Dribble 1/4 cup or so of melted butter or margarine over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten egg whites.
Fold in coconut and Post Toasties.
Add salt and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Let stand on sheet until cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Grease and flour 2 bread pans. Pour batter into pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: carnival cookies
directions: Cream shortening with both sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend well.
Stir in Raisin Bran and oatmeal.
Stir in flour, baking powder and baking soda into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Roll into small balls.
Place on greased baking sheet and press with fork to flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well, then add dried beef and mix. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini sticks
directions: Combine potato flakes, cheese, celery seed, garlic salt and butter.
Dip the zucchini in the eggs and then into the potato mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400 degree for 20 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: dill dip(appetizer)
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Can be served with chips, crackers or your favorite raw vegetables.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: maloogy
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, pepper, celery and garlic in a 12-inch skillet until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and pepper. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in pasta.
Heat through. Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lil' smokies in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Drain liquid from smokies. Roll out biscuits one at a time.
Cut each into 5 strips.
Wrap each strip around each smokie.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray and place wrapped smokies on it.
Bake for 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with mustard.
Serve immediately or can be rewarmed in microwave for 3 minutes on medium.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Layer the foods like this:
Bottom and top layer to have a layer of hamburger.
Can also have a middle layer of hamburger. Top hamburger with sliced raw potatoes, the other vegetables and half of the soups.
Then, repeat layers, ending with the last layer of hamburger.
Bake at 350° for at least 3 hours.
May need to add water.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown ground pork; season with salt and chopped garlic.
Boil chicken; take off bone and cut in small pieces.
Boil shrimp; dice and set aside.
Heat oil in wok or frying pan.
Stir and fry 3 cups vegetables at a time; season and drain.
You will need a very large bowl for mixture.
Should be cool enough to handle, or you can make it ahead of time and refrigerate.
Place handful in corner of wrapper and roll over.
Pull sides together in a triangle; moisten corners and roll again.
Deep fry in hot oil to a golden brown.

title: peppermint meringues
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add gradually sugar at low speed of mixer.
Continue to beat 5 more minutes.
Fold in vanilla, chips and candy.

title: best ever chess pie
directions: Soften butter and beat until fluffy.
Add sugar and cream. Then lemon juice and grated rind.
Add the syrup and the cornstarch, mixed with a little water.
Then add the rest of the water.
Last, beat the 4 egg whites until slightly stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° until firm.
Makes 2 thick pies.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Put Twinkies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Layer pudding over Twinkies. Drain pineapple good, layer over pudding.
Layer sliced bananas next.
Cover all with Cool Whip.
May top with chopped nuts and cherries.
Serve chilled.

title: crandall's favorite fudge
directions: Bring the first 2 ingredients to a rapid boil in a large pan. Boil 9 minutes or to soft ball stage (135°), stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add the chocolate chips, butter or margarine and vanilla.
After blending these ingredients thoroughly at low speed on electric mixer, beat at medium speed for about 10 minutes. It will begin to thicken.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill in refrigerator about 2 hours, until firm.
When firm, cut into pieces.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: green beans with garlic saute
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add beans and cover.
Cook until tender. Mix remainder of ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over hot beans and toss to coat.
Serves 8.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Soak 3 hours in ice water, then drain.
Add sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed, cloves and mustard seed.
Boil until pickles change color.
Can in jars.

title: mexican corn pudding
directions: Mix together ingredients. Bake at 325° like a custard.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.
Melt oleo in pie pan. This will grease pan and melt oleo at same time.

title: crab or chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Thin the mayonnaise with milk and mix in.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Then fold in chow mein noodles and serve on lettuce leaf.
Also good for pita pocket.

title: lasagna(serves 6)
directions: In a medium size non-stick skillet, brown beef.
Drain grease. Add tomatoes or tomato sauce, tomato paste, garlic powder, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: teriyaki
directions: Rub chuck roast with meat tenderizer and place in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Make a marinade from remaining ingredients.
Remove roast from refrigerator; slice into serving size slices.
Place meat in marinade for 4 hours or overnight.
Broil or barbecue meat until done.

title: bailey's chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In 10-inch spring-form pan, mix graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar and butter.
Pat mixture into bottom of pan.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until puffy.
Set aside.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Follow the directions on box of cake mix.
Add pudding mix and chocolate chips. Bake in Bundt pan.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, green peppers, rice and beef. Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan biscuit spirals
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, 2 tablespoons granulated sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter/margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center. Combine egg and milk; add all at once to dry mixture.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently on a lightly floured surface for 15 strokes.
Roll dough into a 15 x 8-inch rectangle. Brush with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Combine pecans and 3 tablespoons brown sugar; sprinkle over dough.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and baking soda. Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in the cheese. Add buttermilk; stir just until the dough clings together. On a slightly floured surface, knead the dough lightly until easy to handle. Roll into a 12-inch circle.
Cut into 8 wedges. Begin at wide end of wedge and roll toward the point. Place biscuits point side down on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in pan.
Cook to a soft-ball stage, 234°.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until it begins to stiffen.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch pan or plate.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: granny clark's potato salad
directions: Wash and cook potatoes, with peeling on.
Let cool, then peel and cut into small chunks.
Add sweet pickles, celery, onion, eggs, sugar, salt, salad dressing, celery seed and mustard.
Mix well. Let set for 1 hour, then refrigerate.
Better the next day.

title: baked beans and vegalinks
directions: Oil rectangular baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Combine ingredients.
Top with can of Vegalinks rolled in oil.
Cook at 350° until bubbling hot.

title: yogurt fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and yogurt.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 8 servings.

title: potato, cucumber and dill salad
directions: Cook the potatoes in pot of boiling water until just tender. Drain.
Transfer to a large bowl. Add 2 tablespoons vinegar to hot potatoes and stir gently.
Combine remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Gradually mix in oil. Add chopped dill.
Mix into potatoes. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 6 hours ahead.
Cover, chill and bring to room temperature before serving.)
Mix in cucumbers. Garnish with dill sprigs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas meatballs and rice
directions: Mix beef, eggs, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High until meatballs are set and lose pink color, 4 to 7 minutes. Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook in microwave at High temperature until mixture is bubbly and onions are tender, 4 to 7 minutes.
Stir after half of cooking time.
Let stand until rice is tender, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: jamie's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Mix egg substitute, nuts, water, applesauce and pumpkin. Pour all at once into dry ingredients; blend lightly. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour. (Test with toothpick.)

title: roly-poly lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare lasagna noodles according to package directions.
In a medium bowl, combine the Ricotta cheese, shredded Mozzarella, egg, spinach and salt.
Place one noodle on work surface and spread 1/2 cup of cheese/spinach mixture over the noodle.
Roll up noodle, jelly roll style.
Repeat with remaining noodles.
Spread 1 cup of tomato sauce over the bottom of a casserole dish.
Place the rolled-up noodles with the seam side down, on the sauce.
Spoon the remaining sauce over the center of each Roly-Poly Lasagna.
Cover lightly with foil and bake 20 minutes, until bubbly.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and Parmesan cheese (if desired).

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Blend in fruit cocktail.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: You can make your own meatballs.
I use ones from Sam's.

title: ground beef-noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck with onions; season to taste with salt, pepper and celery salt and stir well.
Add tomato sauce and simmer while noodles cook in separate saucepan.
When noodles are cooked, stir them in ground beef mixture and oregano.
Pour in casserole dish; top with cheese and place in hot oven, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown the first 8 ingredients together. Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer slowly for about 30 minutes. Add some tomato juice if mixture gets too thick. Grate and add the cheese. Cook slowly for about 30 minutes more.

title: osgood pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together; then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together; pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Tastes similar to mincemeat.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Press into bottom of pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla for 20 minutes until light and fluffy.
Put into pan over graham cracker mixture.
Put pineapple on top.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package. Spread over top.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Refrigerate overnight, uncovered.
Top with cherries before serving.

title: saucy apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, powder, soda, salt and spices.
Blend nuts and raisins with 1 tablespoon sifted dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, then add sugars, blend in egg.
Add applesauce, alternating with sifted dry ingredients.
Blend in floured nuts and raisins.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into lightly greased and floured pan, in 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken pie #3
directions: Cook vegetables until tender; drain.
Combine vegetables with chicken, soups, broth and peas.
Pour into a greased 13 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, milk and butter.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cherries and berries on a cloud
directions: Sprinkle cream of tartar over egg whites.
Beat eggs to soft peaks, adding salt and sugar gradually and beating to stiff peaks. Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 400°; turn off.
Put meringue in and leave overnight.

title: spiced peach salad *
directions: Drain peaches and measure juice.
Heat juice to boiling point. Dissolve Jell-O in hot juice.
Chill.
Soften cream cheese with milk.
Add nuts.
Cut up peaches and add to Jell-O mixture. Congeal until firm.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: peach crisp
directions: Put sliced peaches in baking dish.
Mix and add on top of peaches:
flour, brown sugar, butter, cinnamon and salt.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheerio bars
directions: Combine first three ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Then blend in the peanut butter and Cheerios.
Mix together and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with the melted butterscotch and chocolate chips.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter slowly in saucepan; add flour, cool a few minutes. Slowly add milk, then cheese and salt.
Cook until thickens. Serve with tomato sauce on the side.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together using only enough mayonnaise to hold veggies together.
Chill several hours.
Crunchy and delicious.
You might not even know it's cauliflower if you make the pieces small enough!
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place chicken, celery and onion in a large kettle. Add a quart of water. Simmer until meat is tender. Lift meat from broth and cool. Dice. To the broth, add tomatoes, diced potatoes, meat, beans, corn and sugar. Salt to taste. Simmer slowly, stirring occasionally, for 3 hours. Makes about 6 quarts. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour.
Add coconut and nuts.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 275° oven.
Store cookies in airtight container about 5 days before serving.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and toast bread.
Cut toast into cubes and place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast.
Thoroughly beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla.
Pour mixture over toast; let stand 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight. In the morning, parboil them for 10 minutes with a teaspoon of baking soda.
Then run cold water through the beans in a colander.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and celery in chicken stock.
Boil spaghetti. Drain.
Put all ingredients in large buttered casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: polish sausage with peppers and onions
directions: Cut each
pepper
into	12
wedges.
Cut onion into 1/2 inch thick slices.
Separate into rings.
Cook peppers, onion, garlic and thyme
in oil in large skillet, over medium heat, 8 to	10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove to warm platter. Keep warm.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry or cherry delight pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together until crumbled with fingers or large fork in a large baking pan.
Put in the freezer and let stay until the other ingredients are prepared.
Whip Dream Whip according to direction on package.
Bake two pie shells with the pecans sprinkled on the bottom.
Let cool.
Take the cream cheese mixture out of the freezer and add gradually to whipped Dream Whip and beat in mixer until smooth.
Pour in cooled pie shells and refrigerate until set.
Top with one can of pie filling and serve.
This makes 2 pies.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in bacon.
Grease baking dish and cover bottom with dried beef.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 2 hours.

title: fudge squares
directions: Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
May top with nuts if desired.
Bake for 16 minutes at 400°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain chopped spinach.
Blend with rest of the ingredients.
Chill and serve with rye bread.

title: hot cheese
directions: Grate sharp cheese and mix with cream cheese.
Add crushed nuts and garlic powder.
Shape into two or three long rolls.
Roll in chili powder until well covered.
Roll in wax paper, then Reynolds Wrap.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Chill well.

title: laban(yogurt)
directions: Heat the milk in a stainless steel saucepan, over medium high heat to 180-200°.
Use a candy thermometer.
Do not let the milk scorch or boil over.
Let the milk cool on the stove top to 120°. If the milk cools too much, you can give it a little heat to bring it back up to 120°.
For the starter, you should save some from a previous batch or buy plain, unflavored yogurt from the store.
Be sure to buy a brand that has a live culture such as Dannon's. Wait until the milk has cooled
to 120° or when you can keep your little finger in milk comfortably and count to 10.

In a small bowl, stir 2 tbsp. starter until smooth and add a little of the warm milk to warm the starter and thin it a little. Then thoroughly stir the starter into the pan of warm milk and cover the pan with a lid. Then wrap the pan with layers of clean towels and place in a warm, draft free place for 4 hours. The oven is a good place and you can warm it (not Hot!) a little (about 100°) and turn if off before you put in the pan of yogurt. If the yogurt still has not set in 4 hours, leave it longer and check hourly. If you make it late at night, you can leave it overnight. After it has set, refrigerate immediately.
Excess moisture can be absorbed with paper towels placed on top of the yogurt.
Be sure to save a starter for the next batch. The recipe can easily be doubled when you need a greater quantity for cooking.
Makes 1 quart.

title: tired mom's main dish
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust-lined pie pan. Cover with top crust and crimp edges to seal.
Slit the top crust to vent and brush crust with a little milk.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together flour, butter and pecans.
Pat into the bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar. Roll by hand into 1-inch balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in sugar while hot and again when cooled.

title: microwave wieners
directions: Mix honey and barbecue sauce together.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add cut up hot dogs.
Cook 3 minutes on High in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla; add dry ingredients and apples.
Mix and bake at 350° in large glass baking dish.
Let cool before removing from dish.

title: blender candy bar frosties
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Garnish as desired.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine chicken, tomatoes, potatoes, onion and okra in 5-quart crock-pot.
Set on low; cook 8 hours or until potatoes are tender. Add corn, catsup and barbecue sauce.
Cook 10 more minutes and serve.

title: corn bread supreme
directions: Mix thoroughly first 6 ingredients.
Heat oil until very hot in 7 or 8-inch skillet and add to corn meal mixture.
Pour into skillet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
You may add to this 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese and two jalapeno peppers.
This is a version of Mexican corn bread which is very good.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all together.
This keeps for days or can be frozen.

title: party walnut broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until just barely tender; drain well and place in an oiled 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the margarine in a saucepan.
Stir in the flour; cook briefly, then add milk.
Add the chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside.
Melt the remaining 4 tablespoons margarine in 2/3 cup water.
Mix with the herb dressing and walnuts.
Pour the chicken broth sauce over the broccoli; sprinkle evenly with walnut mixture and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until crusty on top.
Yields 6 servings.
Contains approximately 206 calories per serving.

title: blender banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour and place in mixing bowl.
In blender container, place eggs, shortening, milk, lemon juice, bananas and sugar. Blend until smooth.
Add nuts and blend until well chopped.
Pour over flour and stir lightly together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch loaf pan for 45 minutes or in 3 miniature loaf pans for 30 minutes.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit real good before mixing with other ingredients. Prepare night before and place in refrigerator.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add salt and macaroni; cook until tender.
Drain.
Add margarine or butter, milk and cheese.
Stir until all is melted together.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat.
Add everything else and beat 4 minutes.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325° in tube pan.
(If you want a chocolate pound cake, just add 4 to 6 tablespoons of cocoa when you add the flour.
Also, leave out the lemon.)

title: mother goose popcorn
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla, a little red cake coloring and 1/2 teaspoon soda last thing.
Pour over 5 or 6 quarts popcorn.
Cover good and pour out on cookie sheet to cool.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Dip teaspoon of cookie dough into sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together and add to the following: eggs, evaporated milk, margarine and vanilla.
Mix together well and pour into a pie crust and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown
in
pan	ground beef, bacon and onion.
Pour off fat and put in crock-pot.
Add beans.
To mixture, add remaining ingredients.
Mix
well
in crock-pot.
Cook on low 3 to 4 hours. Or,
if
you
prefer, put mixture in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.	Serves 8.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar into the well beaten eggs.
Blend in margarine.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into an unbaked shell and sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° or until coconut is golden brown.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Mix flour, milk, margarine, sugar and salt together as for pie dough.
Mix egg, water and bouillon.
Add to first mixture.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour twice, adding soda the second time.
Add sour cream and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; bring to boil oleo, oil, water and cocoa. Pour over flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, soda and buttermilk.
Pour batter onto cookie sheet with narrow rim and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring butter and water to a boil and remove from heat.
Then stir in flour and pour into bowl with 4 eggs already beaten; mix with mixer.
Pour into large greased cake pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese and pour on top of cooled crust.
Then spread Cool Whip over top and drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in an ungreased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bert's chili
directions: Brown beef.
Put in the remainder of ingredients and let simmer 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: pan fried cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage and wash.
Lay cabbage in frying pan.
Slice onion, green pepper and potatoes over cabbage.
Pour in water and stripple drippings.
Cook on high until boiled down.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove cover and cook until tender.

title: cranberry salad(especially good with turkey and dressing)
directions: Grind cranberries and cut up orange in food chopper.
Add sugar and let stand in refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Chill until syrupy.
Add all other ingredients and stir well. Chill and stir again.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Best made the day before serving.

title: potato chowder
directions: Saute bacon with chopped onion until bacon is browned and onion is very tender.
Add water, potatoes, salt and pepper. Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add 2 cups milk and heat the chowder until it is very hot, but not boiling.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 300° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: frozen juice punch
directions: Mix ingredients just before serving.
Pour over crushed ice or frozen ice ring.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: bourbon sausages
directions: Mix ketchup, brown sugar and bourbon in a saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Lower heat and allow sauce to thicken, about 30 minutes.
Add sausages and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Sauce may be saved in refrigerator for several days.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

Sift flour, baking powder, and salt together in mixing bowl. 2. Stir in eggs, vanilla extract, and milk continuing to stir until the mixture is smooth. 3. Beat in the flour mixture a little at a time.
Then add oatmeal and raisins stirring until the batter is well blended. 4. Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake for 12 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned on top.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour
and	sugar
in large bowl.
Cook in saucepan until comes
to
boil
margarine,
cocoa	and
water.
Remove immediately and
pour
over
flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add to mixture buttermilk, eggs, cinnamon and soda.
Grease and flour a cookie sheet.
(I use jelly roll pan, 17 x 11 x 3/4-inches.) Pour batter
into
pan.	Bake
at
350°	for 20 to 25 minutes. While cake
is baking combine in saucepan 4 tablespoons cocoa, 1 stick margarine and milk.
Bring to boil and immediately add powdered sugar
and	vanilla.
As
soon
as cake is taken from oven, spread frosting on and sprinkle with crushed walnuts.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add all other ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in square, glass container and let set up in refrigerator until firm.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar (1/2 cup).
Place on wax paper.
Can be stored in well-sealed container.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix the 1/2 cup sugar, salt and gelatin.
Beat egg yolks, lime juice and water together.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Bring to a boil; stir in peel and food coloring.
Chill.

title: ginger muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Let set 5 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and salad oil.
Into mixture, blend flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add undrained pineapple, carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well, but do not overbeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Put mashed potatoes on top of mix.
Broil enough to brown top of potatoes.
Let cool for about 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix.
Bake in 2 loaf pans in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: easy eggplant parmesan
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese and cornmeal.
Dip eggplant into butter; coat with cornmeal mixture.
Place in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread slices with pizza sauce.

title: bacon cheese french bread
directions: Cut bread into 1 inch thick slices.
Place sliced loaf on a large piece of foil.
Combine bacon and cheese.
Place between bread slices.
Drizzle butter over loaf.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla together.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Divide dough.
Roll out and spread filling on dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add milk.
Add flour.
Add bananas.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Fold in nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ice cream butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except for vanilla in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
From the time the sauce comes to a full rolling boil, boil it 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from the burner.
Add the vanilla.
Let cool and serve or pour it into a container.
Will keep in the pantry for 1 week; warm before serving.
Very good over Haagen dazas Vanilla Swiss Almond ice cream.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix and frosting, cooking oil and milk; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Bake in a Bundt pan (greased and floured) 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
tags: Betty Crocker coconut pecan frosting mix

title: baked gouda cheese
directions: Remove crescent roll dough from can and place on cookie sheet. Press perforations together. Remove wax from cheese.
Place cheese in center of dough. Coat cheese with mustard and bring up dough to cover cheese.
Press to seal.
Brush with beaten egg white and sprinkle with seed. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes until nicely browned.
Cut in wedges. Serve immediately.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute leeks and onion in butter; add flour and mix well.
Add chicken broth to potatoes with onion mixture.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are done, about 8 minutes.
Add whipping cream and heat through.

title: mother's busy day beef stew
directions: Brown meat.
Layer in 4-qt. dish with cover as follows (can cover any 4-qt. dish with foil):
browned meat, onion slices, carrots, potatoes, celery, broth, water, pepper, vinegar.
DO NOT STIR.
Cover and bake at 275° 5 to 6 hours.

title: corn fairfax
directions: Saute onion and celery in bacon fat for 5 minutes.
Add corn and beans; cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Blend and stir in milk and eggs.
Pour into shallow baking dish. Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cream cheese frosting for carrot cake
directions: Blend all, mixing well.

title: ranch baked chicken
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in dressing mix, then bake, skin side up, at 325° for 45 minutes until brown and crispy.
Serve and enjoy!

title: rosemary butternut bisque
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place squash on baking sheet and roast until tender, about 25 minutes.
(I sprayed Pam on the baking sheet to prevent sticking.)
Transfer baked squash to large pot and cook with chicken broth, rosemary and orange rind.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Place mixture in food processor and process until smooth.
Stir in salt and pepper. Ladle into bowl and add a bit of cream, if desired, but delicious even without cream.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: happy hour mushrooms
directions: Mix together last 6 ingredients.
Fill mushrooms with cheese mixture.
Spray pan with Pam.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes.

title: fast fixin' fruit 'n' cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour oil into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tilt pan to cover bottom.

Put cake mix, eggs and water into pan. Stir until blended (2 minutes). Scrape sides and spread batter evenly. Spoon pie filling into batter. Use fork to fold into batter just enough to create a marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool cake and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chili-cheese appetizer
directions: In a small saucepan, heat chili until hot.
Scatter chips on a large serving platter.
Layer hot chili, cheese, lettuce and avocado dip on top.
Serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine and mix well.

title: candy salad
directions: Mix together candies and pineapple; let set for 2 hours. Then mix together with remaining ingredients.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend flour, butter and powdered sugar. Press evenly into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes. While crust is baking, beat rest of ingredients together.
Pour over crust and bake for 20 to 25 minutes more.
Do not overbake.

title: soy pecans
directions: Melt butter and pour over pecans on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir 2 to 3 times, then mix soy sauce, Tabasco sauce and Beau Monde.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Cook noodles. Cook cabbage in a separate pan so the cabbage does not dominate the flavor. Toss the two together; heat again after adding the seasonings (salt and pepper).
Very good with Velveeta cheese melted into mixture. This is a good dish if children do not like cabbage but like noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Clean chicken and chop into 2-inch pieces.
Drain chestnuts. Brown chicken in mixture of oil and soy sauce.
After chicken has fried for several minutes, add sherry.
Cook over brisk heat until sherry partly evaporates, then add water chestnuts and water. Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: mint fudge sauce
directions: In medium sauce pan, combine chocolate chips, mint patties, evaporated milk and corn syrup. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until all ingredients are melted. Remove from heat. Stir in butter until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in butter until melted. Serve warm over ice cream. Store covered in refrigerator.

title: vegetable delight
directions: Cook mixed vegetables until tender; drain liquid.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Cover mixture with grated cheese.
Heat in hot oven until cheese is melted and vegetables heated, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft.
Drain off water.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil to raisins.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: my grandmother's quick and easy chili
directions: Cook all together for about 45 minutes.
Add red kidney beans about 10 minutes before done cooking.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli by package direction, omitting salt.
Drain thoroughly.
Place cuts in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Stir soup and cheese together.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise, and egg to soup mix; stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli. Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle evenly over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cut into squares and serve on crackers.

title: carrot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients; mix just until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in margarine until tender. Stir in flour and add water and bouillon.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens and bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Combine 1 cup sauce, chicken, 1 cup cheese and chili powder, mixing well.
Dip each tortilla into remaining sauce to soften.
Fill each with equal portions of chicken mixture.
Roll up.
Arrange in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over enchiladas; sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley.
Bake for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Add egg yolks.
Add the rest.
Chill dough.
Teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets and put 1/2 sticky cherry on top.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan; melt on stove top.
Beat eggs.
Add flour, milk and baking powder. Add cheese, spinach (thawed and drained) and onion; mix well. Spoon into pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool for 45 minutes; cut into squares.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat in chunks in butter; add celery, onion and mushrooms.
Cook for approximately 10 minutes on low. Add soup and mix together. Pour in greased casserole dish. Cover with chinese noodles. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: salsa roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese over tortillas.
Roll tortillas and cut into small segments.
Serve tortillas with salsa for dipping!

title: easy bake chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing 30 minutes.
Melt margarine with Pepperidge dressing mix.
Place cheese over marinated chicken.
Top with dressing mixture, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in thick crosswise slices.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Coat with dry mixture.
Drop into hot fat until golden brown.
This has been passed on down from generation.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and milk.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, combine egg, oil and oatmeal mixture.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten. Fill buttered muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen. Enjoy!

title: mamie eisenhower's favorite fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Bring to a vigorous boil, stirring often, then reduce heat and simmer 6 minutes. Meanwhile place remaining ingredients (except pecans) in a large bowl.
Gradually pour boiling syrup over the chocolate-marshmallow mixture; beat until chocolate is melted.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into buttered pans and store in a cool place several hours to harden before cutting in squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Put in buttered casserole and refrigerate overnight. Remove 1 hour before baking; sprinkle with potato chips and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: lo-cal zucchini puff
directions: Stir together eggs, oil and oleo and add to Bisquick.
Mix in rest of ingredients and 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Very good! Stuffing-like recipe.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; sift together twice.
Combine sugar and oil in a mixing bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Add carrots; blend well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla; then add dry ingredients gradually.
Blend well.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 10-inch greased tube pan or a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and frost.

title: basil (pesto) sauce
directions: Hand mix until smooth or may be prepared in blender. Use as sauce over 1 pound pasta or noodles.

title: maple butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine brown sugar, oleo and vanilla and mix well.
Add beaten eggs, half at a time, and mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
Blend very well.
Stir in nuts.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine sifted flour with salt.
Add alternately with butter and milk.
Add vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add cocoa paste.
Fold in vinegar and soda.
Pour batter in equal parts into 3 cake pans, greased, then with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh as spring salad
directions: In a medium bowl, mix gelatine with sugar.
Add boiling water; stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
With wire whip or beater, blend mayonnaise, Italian dressing and lemon juice. Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 9-inch mold; chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: louisiana crawfish casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in crawfish, soup, rice, parsley, lemon juice and seasoning.
Add bread, which has been crumbled and soaked in milk; mix well.
Spoon into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Baked at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: arcadia park united methodist church's toasted coconut cake
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in a saute pan or skillet over medium heat; allow the remaining portion to soften at room temperature.
Add the coconut and pecans to skillet and stir constantly until the mixture is golden brown (watch carefully not to scorch it).
Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Mix the cake mix according to package directions, adding 1 cup of the toasted coconut and pecans.
Divide the batter among three 8-inch round pans and bake and cool according to package directions.
The extra layer seems to make the cake moist and "special."

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add onion, green pepper, and celery.
Cook until vegetables are tender and can be easily pierced with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: no guilt mud pie
directions: Blend graham cracker crumbs, sugar, chocolate mix and liquid butter.
Press into a deep dish pie pan that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Pour softened yogurt into pie crust. Place in freezer at least for 1 hour.
Spread fudge topping on top.
Freeze at least 30 minutes.

title: seafood salad dressing
directions: Mix in order listed.
Pour over favorite salad to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add all dry ingredients.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook bacon in large Dutch oven and set aside.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons fat. One at a time, place roasts in Dutch oven and brown on all sides.
Remove from pan. Add onions, garlic, apples and carrots.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add the rest (minus the roasts) and simmer 5 minutes.
Add roasts to pot. Cover tightly with foil. Roast for 3 to 4 hours until meat is tender. Stir and baste occasionally.
Remove roasts to platter. Let rest for 15 minutes before slicing.
If sauerkraut is too juicy, place pot on burner on medium-high for a minute, stirring constantly.
Place alternating slices of roast around platter. Heap sauerkraut in center and garnish with bacon pieces. Serve with sour cream mashed potatoes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Measure dry ingredients into very large bowl.
Combine with a slotted spoon.
Measure moist ingredients into another very large bowl.
Use electric mixer to combine moist ingredients.
Combine moist ingredients with dry ingredients, using a slotted spoon. Pour batter into a container with a tight fitting lid and store in refrigerator.
Batter keeps for 6 weeks in refrigerator.
To bake, grease muffin tins with butter or use Pam spray.
(Don't use paper liners; they stick to muffins.)
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator sweet rolls
directions: Add shortening and sugar to scalded milk; stir until dissolved.
Pour cooled milk mixture into large mixing bowl to cool.
Dissolve yeast and salt in water.
When yeast mixture starts to froth, mix with milk mixture.
Add beaten eggs to mixture and beat vigorously, using portable mixer or wooden spoon. Begin adding flour, one cup at a time, mixing until you have a stiff batter.
Add a total of 6 cups of flour, one cup at a time until you have a stick batter.
Place sticky dough on floured surface and knead in remaining flour or enough flour to make dough elastic and smooth.
This process takes about 5 to 10 minutes. Dough will be tacky to touch.

title: grandma's pork-fried rice
directions: Use recipe for Minute Rice (number of servings you prefer). Dice pork chops and fry in small amount of oil (number of pork chops depend on servings of rice).
Add green onions to pork chops and mushrooms; simmer for a few minutes.
Mix rice with pork chop mixture and simmer on low heat, about 3 to 5 minutes; stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
(This can also be prepared in a wok.)
Serve over chow-mein noodles; sprinkle with soy sauce.

title: batter curls
directions: Make batter, beating well until smooth.
Pour into a squeeze mustard or catsup bottle.
Squeeze into hot grease in a circular motion.
Fry until lightly brown and crisp.
Drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar or confectioners sugar.
May also be served for breakfast with syrup and butter.

title: mom's refrigerator relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over the cucumber mixture (do not cook this). Keep in gallon jar in refrigerator. Will keep a long time.

title: herb rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except biscuits in pie pan.
Place in hot oven to melt; stir.
Cut biscuits in half and swish each piece in herb mixture and arrange each piece so that each touches in pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: escarole and bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, place chicken broth and escarole.
Be sure it is washed and coarsely cut.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Gently brown the garlic in the oil.
Add the cannellini beans and their liquid and heat thoroughly.
Combine with the escarole and let simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.
Stir carefully with a wooden spoon.
This should have a soupy consistency; add more broth or water if necessary.
Serve with red pepper flakes and fresh grated cheese.
Hot Italian bread is necessary to soak up all flavor.

title: garbage cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together; cream oil, butter, sugars and egg.
Add dry ingredients slowly; keep mixing.
Add chips last. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 12 to 14 minutes.

title: scottish oatcakes
directions: Put oatmeal, flour and salt in a bowl and mix.
Make a well in the center and pour in the hot melted shortening and cold water. Mix well and then roll into small balls with floured hands, to prevent sticking.
Roll out each ball and cut into fourths.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven, for about 20 minutes.

title: traditional martini(alcoholic drink)
directions: Into 16 ounce mixing glass, pour wine, then add gin and ice. Stir 15 to 20 times.
Strain into glass.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill overnight.
You can substitute tuna or turkey for chicken in recipe.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Peel and/or cut fruit as appropriate.
Mix all ingredients. Preparation time: 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 10, depending on how much fruit, seasonal varieties, size, etc.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan (ungreased). Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; cut in butter.
Pack on top of apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into two 8-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm and brown.

title: w. va. mud pies
directions: Combine dirt
and
water.
Stir
75 times, until mixed. Take mixture and divide in half.
Place on hot rock in sun and bake for 1 hour.
Wipe hands on clothes and show mom.

title: endless coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and peppers and combine with onion; set aside.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing ingredients well and pour over coleslaw mix.

title: sorghum cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in oleo.
Make a well and add sorghum, then hot water mixed with soda.
Add eggs and chips and mix well.
Form dough in long 1-inch thick rolls on cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375°.
When done baking, cut and put out to cool.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: In a large container, mix together all ingredients except crackers.
Blend well.
Stir in crackers and let sit, stirring occasionally, until all liquid is absorbed.
Serve.
Store at room temperature in covered container.

title: hearty blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients, reserving 2 tablespoons sugar. Combine cooled butter, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Gently stir in berries. Spoon into muffin tins lined with paper or brushed with butter. Sprinkle tops with reserved sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from tin.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: mandarin dijon chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts generously with Dijon pepper and chicken soup mix.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Add vegetable oil.
Place skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add chicken to skillet and cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients into pan and cook until cabbage is tender. Potatoes may be added.

title: asparagus with sesame butter
directions: Place asparagus spears in large skillet.
Add boiling water and salt.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove asparagus and keep warm. Drain cooking liquid, reserving 1/2 cup in small saucepan.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
While rice is cooking, spray a large skillet.
On medium heat, add kielbasa, onion, pepper and celery; saute.
Add tomatoes and hot pepper sauce; drain rice and add ingredients together.
Cook thoroughly.

title: caramel brownies
directions: First, unwrap caramels and place in medium bowl.
Add evaporated milk and microwave for 2 minutes.
Take out and stir until smooth.

title: corn sticks
directions: Mix and sift flour, cornmeal, soda and salt.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until well mixed.
Stir into butter.
Turn into greased bread stick pans and bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Combine ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Strain and serve hot. Sweeten with sugar or honey to taste.

title: baked chicken livers
directions: Cut livers into bite size pieces.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and parsley together.
Dip pieces of liver in melted butter, then into cheese and crumb mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate buttermilk sheet cake
directions: Note:
To
make buttermilk, add 1/2 teaspoon vinegar in 1/2 cup milk.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Boil for 1 hour, then can.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir well.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in the 1/2 cup of water and let stand 10 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar, add salt, warm water and dissolved yeast.
Add enough flour so that dough can be well kneaded.
Knead until dough is elastic to touch.
Let stand in warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Let rise about 2 hours before baking.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples in unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Spoon over apple slices, dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Seal edges, cut slits in top. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 5 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix dressing with margarine; remove to bowl.
Cook squash and onion until tender. Drain and add soup and sour cream.
Layer squash and stuffing (2 layers each); begin with squash and end with stuffing.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Stir in breadcrumbs and crabmeat and shape into 8 (2 1/2-inch) patties.
Place on a baking sheet lined with wax paper.
Chill 30 minutes.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium high heat until hot.
Add crab cakes.
Cook 3 minutes on each side or until browned.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Saute Bell peppers, onion and celery in butter.
Boil chicken with salt and pepper.
Retrieve the chicken, save the water to boil the noodles in.
Chop the chicken, set aside.
Drain the noodles, set aside.
Combine velveeta cheese, Rotel, chicken soup and English peas.
Put all together in a large baking pan.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.
You can put this in a crock pot to keep warm.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Stir all together. May add nuts if desired. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze. Remove 15 to 20 minutes before serving to soften slightly. Slice and serve on lettuce. May freeze in individual muffin cups.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix walnuts, flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves; set aside. Mix eggs, sugar and butter in a processor about 1 minute.
Add bananas and lemon juice and mix well.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Bake 1 hour.

title: easy mustard gravy
directions: Mix mustard and water.
Heat, add butter and melt, then add rest of ingredients.
Heat on low boil for 1/2 hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: peach delight
directions: Roll peach halves in vanilla wafer crumbs until well coated. Place halves, cut side down, in sherbet glasses.
Top peach halves with spoonful of whipped cream and walnuts.

title: elaine's crawfish fettucini
directions: Melt butter in large heavy saucepan.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Cook 10 minutes until clear.
Add flour; blend in well.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add parsley and crawfish tails.
Cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add cream, cheese, jalapenos and garlic.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, covered, on low heat 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and add sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter. Add rest of the ingredients. Bake in a 9-inch pie crust at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple dandy salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add chopped raw apples, crushed pineapple, pecans and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all
ingredients,
except walnuts.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped walnuts.

title: sweet potato relish
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, but not mushy and drain.
Butter baking dish generously.
Put a layer of potatoes, then half of the sugar, then raisins, pineapple and nuts alternately in layers until all ingredients are used.
Over the top, sprinkle with salt and dot with butter.
Bake in oven 30 minutes.
Good with cold lunches or hot dinners.

title: grandmother's custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in sugar.
Add salt, nutmeg and milk. Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake about 40 minutes or until silver knife inserted into side of filling comes out clean.
Center is still soft, but sets later.
Cook in 450° oven for first 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° to finish baking.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Add milk until good spreading consistency.
Spread on top of graham crackers and return to refrigerator.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: japanese rice medley
directions: Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add water to reserved mushroom liquid to make 1 3/4 cups.
In a saucepan, blend water mixture into gravy mix.
Add mushrooms, rice, vegetables, onion, margarine and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender. Turn into a serving bowl and sprinkle with almonds.

title: lorene staggs' plain cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Can be baked in a large layer pan or 3 layers and stack.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
On second, third and fourth day, knead like bread and refrigerate.
Maintain refrigeration between kneadings.
On the fifth day, form into a log, 2 1/2 to 3-inches in diameter. Place on broiler rack above broiler pan filled with 1-inch of water.
Bake at 150° for 8 hours.
Turn often to maintain even baking.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then add pineapple.
Stir in bread.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold.

title: lima beans creole
directions: Mix lima beans, soup, onion and green pepper.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with sausage links.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Cube cheese and mix with sauce or salsa.
Heat in microwave for 5 minutes or in saucepan on stove for 10 minutes until cheese has melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in a 3-quart pan.
Cook to a hard ball stage (260°).
Beat egg whites in large mixing bowl until stiff.
Gradually beat in boiling syrup.
Add vanilla. Continue beating until mixture will hold its shape when dropped from spoon.
Add nuts or cherries.
Drop on wax paper from teaspoon.

title: lentil salad
directions: In large saucepan, combine lentils, water, onions, cloves, bay leaves, garlic cloves, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon red pepper sauce.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer covered for 30 to 40 minutes, until lentils are tender.
Drain.
Add oil, vinegar, parsley, remaining 1 teaspoon salt and remaining 1/2 teaspoon red pepper sauce.
Mix well and cool.
Stir in celery and onion. Cover and chill several hours.
Turn into bowl lined with salad greens; garnish with tomato wedges.

title: beef strips in tomato sauce(microwave)
directions: Prepare noodles, rice or toast points conventionally while microwaving beef.
In 2-quart casserole, toss together meat, flour and soup mix. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High 5 minutes. Stir. Reduce power to 50% (Medium).
Microwave 15 to 20 minutes or until meat is tender, stirring after half the cooking time.
Stir and let stand 5 minutes. Serve over toast points, noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, syrup, and butter.
Add eggs and pecans to mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 30-35 minutes.

title: alice's original 3-bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Rinse kidney beans and drain again on paper towels.
Combine beans, onion rings, salt, pepper and sugar in a deep bowl.
Warm vinegar but do not boil.
Stir in oil and pour over beans.
Toss lightly, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain and serve in a bowl, surround salad with crisp greens, cherry tomatoes or tomato wedges.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: twinkies delight
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthways.
Place in the bottom of the dish.
Mix together the condensed milk, pudding mix, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour this over the Twinkies.
Pour thawed strawberries and juice on top of the filling.
Refrigerate overnight or for a few hours before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Mix with Pretzels.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
When Jell-O begins to set, pour over top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until firm (overnight).

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni; drain.
Add eggs and stir to mix.
Add cheese; stir to mix.
Add milk and margarine; stir to mix.

title: pork casserole
directions: Dredge pork with flour.
Heat oil in a large pan until sizzling.
Add pork and cook until browned, stirring occasionally. Remove pork to casserole.
Drain excess oil from pan.
Pour into pan the cider or chicken stock.
Heat, stirring, to remove browned particles.
Put all ingredients together with pork.
Cover and bake at 325° for approximately 2 hours or until done.

title: cranberry colada
directions: In large container, combine cranberry, apple juice and lemonade concentrate.
Add water.
Chill until serving.
Before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Garnish with fruit.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: In olive oil saute until translucent the garlic, onions and pepper.
Add mushrooms; cook 3 minutes.
Drain and reserve juice from clams; add clam juice and wine to mixture in pan.
Cook 10 minutes with cover off over medium-high heat or until mixture is reduced by half.
Stir in clams, basil, thyme and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over linguine in a large bowl and toss well. Sprinkle with lots of chopped parsley, 1/2 to 1 cup.

title: company tuna bake
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Blend cream cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir in tuna, pimento, onion, mustard, milk and the macaroni.
Put mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix half dry bread crumbs and melted margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crunchy granola
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, bran, wheat germ, coconut, nuts and salt in a large bowl; set aside.
Put oil, peanut butter, honey, water and vanilla in a saucepan and warm, only until well mixed.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly with hands.
Mixture should be crumbly.
Add more water for bigger crumbs.
Put into 2 large flat pans and bake at 250° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn every 15 minutes.
You may add 1 to 2 teaspoons cinnamon, sesame or sunflower seeds or 1 to 2 tablespoons powdered milk gives a good flavor.

title: elephant ears
directions: Heat, do not boil, milk, sugar and shortening until shortening is melted.
Add yeast and flour and mix until smooth.
Let rise about 30 minutes.

title: krautburgers
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add cabbage and onion and cook until soft, stirring often so it doesn't scorch.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Roll dough thin and cut into 4 or 4 1/2-inch squares.
On these squares, put a heaping teaspoonful of filling and bring up 4 corners; tightly pinch edges.
Place on greased cookie sheet with pinched side down.
Let raise again on cookie sheet and bake at 425° the first 10 minutes, then decrease heat to 350° and bake 20 more minutes.
Serve hot with salad and plenty of hot coffee.
They will be crisp, but cover with a towel after you have removed them from the cookie sheet.

title: chocolate brownie cake
