directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan. Sift sugar, baking soda and flour together.
Bring butter, cocoa and water to a boil. Mix boiled ingredients into dry ingredients. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix again for about 2 minutes. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Cook frosting while cake is baking.

title: pear honey
directions: Mix together.
Bring to boil slowly on medium or medium-low heat.
Boil for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally to make sure it doesn't scorch.
Test for doneness by placing a spoonful on a saucer, placing in freezer, about 3 minutes.
If it's like jelly, it's done.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Great on oatmeal muffins.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice, oil, onion and garlic over medium heat in large skillet until rice is browned.
Add remaining spices, tomato sauce, water and vegetables.
Cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes until water is absorbed.
Reduce to low and cover last 5 minutes for fluffy rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: * Substitute low-salt when possible.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients to hamburger mixture.
Stir well and simmer until spaghetti is done.
Serve sauce over cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: mexico cornbread
directions: Use a saucepan and brown ground beef; drain well.
In same saucepan mix brown ground beef, taco mix, corn and 1/3 cup water. Mix together and simmer on medium heat.
Follow direction on cornbread mix.
Use a 9 x 9 pan or glass dish, pour a layer of cornbread mix and then a layer of beef mix.
Last layer will be top off with cornbread mix.
Bake on 350 degrees until brown and done. Let cool and serve.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain fruit well.
Cut fruit into small pieces.
Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into pie shells. Decorate top of pie with additional pecan halves and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs and half and half together.
Scramble over medium heat in butter in large skillet.
Put scrambled eggs in 3-quart shallow casserole, which has been sprayed with nonstick coating (Pam).

title: strawberry cake with chantilly cream
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar until light, about 12 to 15 minutes, at medium-high
speed.
Add vanilla and eggs one at a time, beating well	after each.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add	to
creamed
mixture
alternately
with
milk, beating after each	addition.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, dry yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat milk and water until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients and beat well.
Stir in the remaining flour.
This will make a stiff batter.
Grease 2 loaf pans and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Divide dough into the 2 pans.
Sprinkle top of the loaves with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, draft-free for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: sour cream ganache frosting
directions: In a double boiler set over hot water or in a microwave on High power, stirring every 10 seconds, melt the chocolate.
Remove from the heat and add the sour cream.
Stir with a rubber spatula until uniform in color.
If the pan feels warm, transfer to a bowl.

title: stir crazy wacky cake
directions: Put flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch metal baking dish.
Stir with a fork to mix well.
Form 3 wells in the mixture.
Pour oil into 1 well, vinegar in 1 and vanilla in the last.
Pour coffee over all ingredients and stir with a fork until mixed well.
Do not overbeat.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This cake is great with German chocolate frosting.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms and bring to a boil. Add about 1 pound mushrooms and simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Flavor improves if let set for a few hours.
Is best when prepared with fresh mushrooms.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Unroll crescent dough into a rectangle; press into bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Seal seams and perforations. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Mix well.
Add shrimp and toss in mixture until coated.
Broil approximately 4 to 5 minutes or until done and lightly brown.
Serve over rice.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and remove skins.
Cut in half lengthwise and arrange in a buttered baking dish.
Season with salt.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix cookies and melted margarine well (by hand) and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan to make a crust (save 3/4 cup crumbs to sprinkle on top).
Blend remaining ingredients; spread on top of crust and sprinkle remaining 3/4 cup cookie crumbs on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: enchilada casserole(tastes like enchiladas with less trouble.)
directions: Make ground meat into your favorite chili.
Butter an oblong oven dish, then in alternate layers add chili, lay on tortillas and sprinkle with grated cheese until pan is almost full to top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Press out all of the water.
Add remaining ingredients to spinach and mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Cut the top center portion out of the Hawaiian bread. Core loaf out.
Spoon in the spinach dip before serving.
Serve the dip with the cored out bread or crackers and fresh bite-size vegetables.

title: alma's easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, half and half and corn syrup in a Dutch oven or heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugars dissolve.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and cook to soft ball stage (235°), stirring occasionally.
Do not undercook.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Toast bread in oven.
In bowl, mix eggs, Milnot and a little salt.
In another bowl, put oysters, salt them and turn.
Heat chicken broth.
Mix a little hot chicken broth in eggs and Milnot. Put oysters in this.
Crumble bread and put oysters and egg mixture in and then pour boiling broth over bread.
Taste for salt and pepper.
Add a lump of butter.
Heat at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend together milk, egg yolks and lemon juice.
Pour into an 8-inch pie pan lined with an unbaked crumb crust, then cover with meringue or whipped cream.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.

title: granola
directions: Place oatmeal in mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350 for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring often, crumble.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients. Add remaining (not filling) ingredients and mix well.
Spread half the batter on an ungreased cookie sheet. Cover mixture with can of pie filling. Add other half of batter over filling. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 50 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Put ice cubes in cup of water before measuring.
Spoon flour into measuring cup lightly.
Level without shaking or packing down.

title: tiny's slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots.
Mix vinegar and sugar and then combine with mayonnaise.
Toss dressing with cabbage and carrots. Chill.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cream first sugar and oleo.
Sift next three ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch round cake pan.
Combine last sugars and cocoa. Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake 30-40 minutes in 350° oven.
When done, turn cake upside down while hot. Can be served hot or cold.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and peanut butter chips over low heat.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Stir, then empty into a bag containing powdered sugar and shake until coated.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix dry ingrediets together (sifting not necessary).
Add wet ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 t 20 minutes.
Produces pale, soft-like cookies. Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: rice and spinach salad
directions: Cook rice with bay leaf and lemon.
When done, fluff rice and add Italian dressing, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate.

title: peach pie
directions: In a deep heat resistant bowl or loaf pan, melt margarine.
Mix together flour, 1/2 cup sugar and milk.
Mix separately the fruit and 1 cup sugar.
Pour batter in margarine.
Pour fruit on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchie pie
directions: Place margarine in an 11-inch pie pan and let melt.
Make a batter of the brown sugar, flour and buttermilk and pour into the pan with the melted margarine.
Pour the 2 cups of drained fruit on the batter.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.
(If using sour cherries, add 1/2 cup white sugar.)

title: granny's dumplings
directions: In large bowl mix boiling broth and Crisco and salt.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, white and brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, soda and pudding mix with electric mixer until creamy. Add flour, then chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: low-fat spice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.
Contains .66 grams of fat per cookie.

title: cabbage chowder
directions: Cook carrots and celery in large Dutch oven or soup pot, covered for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes; cook 10 minutes longer.
Do not drain.

title: no-bake popcorn cookies
directions: In a saucepan over hot water, melt caramels mixed with marshmallows and orange juice; cool, then add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Spoon
onto aluminum foil and shape into 3-inch circles 1/2-inch thick.
Nuts on top may be added.

title: kendra's applesauce
directions: Steam apples in a steamer pan until soft and mushy.
Then run apples through a sieve and add sugar and cinnamon to taste. Reserve liquid and run through a cheesecloth and there you have apple juice.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, combine cocoa, water and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and soda.
Add chocolate mixture and stir until smooth. Add buttermilk and slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased oblong baking dish and bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf and place in baking dish or pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked bananas
directions: Slice bananas lengthwise.
Cut in half.
Place in casserole; squeeze lemon juice over bananas.
Cover the bananas with brown sugar.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until tender. Turn over once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Combine ingredients.
Beat with mixer 3 minutes.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Ice when cool or serve with Cool Whip.
It is moist and good.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together in morning everything but the potato chips and grated cheese.
Cover and set in the refrigerator.
Just before baking, mix together potato chips and grated cheese and put on top of chicken salad.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, cereal, milk and vanilla; mixing well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with small bits of butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate clair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13 pan with graham crackers. Mix pudding with milk. Beat 2 to 3 minutes on medium speed. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 the mixture over the graham crackers. Layer the crackers and pudding, ending with graham crackers. Remove seal from icing and heat in microwave until soft. Pour over crackers and refrigerate overnight. The longer it sits, the better.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix and serve on crisp lettuce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brown bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients; mix with whole wheat flour and add last 3 ingredients.
Put in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan (or coffee can for round slices).
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Beat margarine until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with eggs.
Use your favorite flavoring (I use 2 teaspoons vanilla and 1 teaspoon almond).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Put cut up bread in 8-inch square greased pan.
Mix eggs, salt, milk, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Pour over bread pieces. Sprinkle with spices.
Add raisins or coconut before liquids. Serve warm.

title: swiss christmas trees
directions: Melt honey and shortening together over hot water.
Add sugar and fruit juice and stir until dissolved.
Add grated rinds of orange and lemon, chopped almonds and the dry ingredients (which have been sifted together).
Chill in refrigerator.

title: mexican fish bake
directions: Cut vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
Place fish, skin side down on a large sheet of tin foil.
Put butter pats on top.
Add salsa and vegetables.
Create a tent with the foil to completely cover the fish and vegetables, leaving room to steam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until fish is done.
Serve with or over rice.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in a tightly closed container.
Mix 4 tablespoons of mix in one cup hot water.

title: rye bread pizzas
directions: Brown sausage and beef together.
Salt and pepper; drain grease.
Add seasonings and cubed Velveeta cheese.
Mix and stir until cheese is melted (over burner on medium).
Spoon mixture onto rye bread slices.
Should make 20 to 24.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 425° until golden, approximately 15 minutes.
Serve hot!! Enjoy.

title: debbie's beef n' potato casserole
directions: Place Tater Tots on bottom and sides of 8 x 12-inch casserole. Bake uncovered at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef and drain. Place beef, broccoli and 1/2 can of the onions in the potato shell. Combine soup, milk and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Pour over beef mixture. Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered for 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: sesame chicken salad
directions: Combine lettuce, chicken,
green onions, celery, sesame seed and almonds in a
salad
bowl.
Toss
with dressing until coated. Place on chilled salad plates and top with additional slivered almonds.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown pork sausage; drain.
Set aside.
Mix soup mix, chicken bouillon cubes, rice and water.
Let boil for 7 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter snack
directions: Take crackers and spread peanut butter on them.
Then take marshmallows and put four to a cracker on it.
Put in microwave until marshmallows are melted.
(Great for kids' snacks.)

title: sausage and tortellini toss
directions: Boil tortellini 15 minutes. Cut sausage into bite-size pieces. Add broccoli and sausage to tortellini. Bring to boil again, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes; drain. Melt margarine in microwave; add cornstarch, then milk. Cook until thickened. Fold in cheese, stirring until smooth. In a large casserole, combine tortellini and sauce; toss until well coated. Serve warm.

title: nutty chocolate bananas
directions: You also need 8 wooden skewers, sharp ends cut off.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Cream butter and sugar. Slowly blend in flour and vanilla. Gently fold into potato chips. Drop dough by well rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten cookies gently with a wet fork. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until barely browned. Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in pan.
(Use wooden spoon.) Blend in milk gradually, then egg yolks.
Add butter.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add almost all the coconut (leave a little to go over the meringue).
Pour into 8-inch baked pie shell and cover with meringue and bits of coconut.
Brown.

title: oat pancakes
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Make a well in the center. Combine last four ingredients; pour into the well and stir until moistened.

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Spread ribs, meaty side up, in a single layer in a large shallow pan.
Brown in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain off fat.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all except last 3 ingredients together, then mix last 3 ingredients; add to pea salad and mix well.
(Peanuts are optional.)

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all together and place in ovenproof dish. Bake at 275° until bubbly. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Salad is low carb and addicting!

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Once oven reaches desired temperature, melt margarine in glass 9X13 inch baking pan. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder. Pour reserved peach juice into dry ingredients and stir until smooth. Remove glass pan from oven and pour batter into pan starting in center; batter will then spread itself over entire pan. Add peaches by placing them in center of pan; allow them to spread on their own. Bake cobbler in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown on top. Do not overcook.

title: biscuit bears
directions: For each bear, shape a biscuit into an oval for the body and place on a greased baking sheet.

title: touchdown dip
directions: Cook ground beef. Mix cream of mushroom soup, chili, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and cheese together in crock-pot. Add ground beef. Let cook until hot. Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: vegetable pita pocket sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut pita bread in half and fill with 1 cup of filling.
Heat for about 10 minutes in 350° oven. Serve at once.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; set aside.
Peel, core and slice apples to make 5 to 6 cups.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine brown sugar, syrup, margarine and cream of tartar in saucepan and bring to hard boil, stirring until sugar is melted. Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda; stir well. Pour over popped corn and mix well. Place in roaster pan and bake in preheated oven at 250° for 1 hour. Store in airtight container.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Mix together tuna, mushroom soup, celery soup, celery, and Soy sauce in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil and turn off.
Bake Chow Mein noodles at 350° for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over Chow Mein noodles.

title: german wine cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg yolks 1 at a time and mix thoroughly. Mix in jam. Stir together buttermilk and soda and add to first mixture. Sift together flour, salt and spices. Add to creamed mixture alternately with wine. Add nuts. Carefully fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cucumber sandwiches(english tea fixings)
directions: Note:
It's necessary to "sweat" the cucumbers first to avoid soggy sandwiches.

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Combine tomatoes and sugar and boil gently, approximately 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add jello and cook 10 minutes longer. Continue to stir.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Process in boiling water or use paraffin wax on top.

title: savory baked chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix well. Pour over cut chicken.
Chill for several hours.
Reserve salad dressing mixture.
Bake chicken, skin side up on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.
Brushing occasionally with salad dressing mixture.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs and shortening. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar and
brown sugar.
Cover 5 cups (approximately 8 peaches)
sliced
fresh
peaches
with sugar mixture. Let stand 1 hour.
Drain,
reserving juice.
Combine in small saucepan cornstarch, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually add reserved peach juice, blending until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly
until thick and clear.
Remove from heat. Add 1
tablespoon lemon juice and sliced peaches.
Turn into unbaked pie
shell,
dot
with
tablespoon
butter (or oleo). Either make
crisscross
over
filling to form lattice top or make crumb
topping.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (may take longer).

title: strawberry tiffany torte
directions: Combine wafer crumbs and margarine; reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture onto the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
To softened cream cheese gradually add 1/2 cup milk, mixing until well blended.
Add pudding mix, remaining milk and lemon rind.
Beat slowly, about 1 minute.
Pour carefully over crust and then cover with sliced strawberries.
Spread Cool Whip over the strawberries and top with remaining wafer crumbs.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: cho na-mool(korean cabbage salad)
directions: Mix and pour over vegetables.
Serve warm or refrigerated. Serves 6.

title: fried cabbage supreme
directions: Fry meat in a large pan.
Add onion, garlic, potatoes and cabbage.
Simmer until mixture turns light brown, stirring frequently.
Pour in chicken broth.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover. Simmer until brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Whip
the heavy cream.	Fold in all ingredients.
Chill overnight.	Serves 8.

title: apple cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Alternately mix in with sour cream. Stir in diced apple.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: travis house cookies
directions: Beat egg white to stiff froth.
Add brown sugar and continue beating.
Stir in flour and salt.
Then add chopped pecans.
Drop by small spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Remove from tin when partly cooled.
Very rich; serve with ice cream or fruit.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: italian tomato sauce(serves 6)
directions: Fry onion, garlic and celery slowly in the oil about 5 minutes.
Crush tomatoes.
Add to paste and the onion, celery and garlic.
Add all other ingredients and simmer in a heavy covered pan 1 hour.
Then add the meat balls and simmer, covered, about 30 minutes longer.
(Cooked mushrooms may be added last 15 minutes.) If sauce becomes too thick, add a little water.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Trim ends only off oranges and cut into quarters.
Core apple and cut apple into quarters.
Wash cranberries.
Put all ingredients except pecans and sugar into blender or processor until mixed well and chopped fine.
Stir in sugar and pecans.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: salmonburgers
directions: Combine salmon, oats, onion, egg, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 4 patties. Brown on both sides in oil in skillet; drain.
Serve on sandwich buns with lettuce and tomato.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and refrigerate until firm.

title: mexican cornbread skillet
directions: Combine eggs, corn meal, soda, salt, corn, milk and oil in a bowl and set aside.
Saute ground beef; drain and set aside.
Pour half of corn bread mixture into a greased 10 1/2-inch skillet. Sprinkle evenly with beef, cheese, onions and peppers.
Pour remaining corn meal mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together. Set aside. Mix oil, eggs and vanilla. Add to apples mixture. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Mix slowly into apple mixture. Pour into a 13 x 9 greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sauce for paper thin sliced ham
directions: Brown onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add the rest of the ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over paper thin sliced ham.

title: oriental seafood stir-fry
directions: Advance preparation:
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender, but still firm, about 7 minutes.
Drain noodles well. Meanwhile, in large saucepan, cook chopped green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in cream of shrimp soup and milk; heat, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Add shredded cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in drained shrimp and drained noodles.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover. Refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Toss together soft bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted butter or margarine.
Wrap and chill.

title: *lemon sauce
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch, salt and nutmeg.
Gradually add boiling water, stirring constantly, and cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until thick and clear.
Add butter or margarine, lemon juice and lemon.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, 1 cup cheddar cheese, sour cream, soup and salt and pepper in a large pot on the stove. In a casserole dish melt butter and place mixture in dish. Add remaining cheese and milk. Bake @ 350 degrees for 1 hr.

title: hawaiian sauce
directions: Mix together and pour over meat; cook until tender, about 2 hours, at 350°.

title: raisin-nut oat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat sugar and egg together until light and fluffy. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on an oiled baking sheet and bake 9 minutes or until tops are golden. Cool on baking sheet several minutes, then carefully remove to a rack. Makes about 18 cookies.

title: angel lime dessert
directions: Trim brown crumbs from cake and tear into bite-size pieces or cut into cubes.
Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add lime juice and food coloring; chill until partially thickened. Fold in whipped cream and coconut.
Place half the cake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour half of gelatin mixture over; repeat layers.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Cut in squares.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes thin.
Add salt; cover with crushed ice.
Let set 15 minutes or until ice melts.
Combine remaining ingredients. Drain cucumbers.
Put cukes into mixture and bring to boil.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: In a skillet or blazer pan of chafing dish, melt the butter. Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in cream and milk; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Reduce heat of skillet.
Stir small amounts of sauce into egg yolks until completely blended.
Return to skillet and cook, stirring constantly.
About 1 minute after returning to skillet, add shrimp, wine and lemon juice; heat thoroughly.
Serve over toast.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: autumn tossed salad
directions: In large salad bowl pour 1/4 cup of salad dressing and 1/2 of the Blue cheese.
Mash Blue cheese into dressing; blend until smooth.
Add lettuce, apple slices and onion.
Crumble remaining Blue cheese on top.

title: raisins and nut bread
directions: Sprinkle flour over raisins and nuts.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt, raisins and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm. Sprinkle with sugar and chopped nuts.

title: smothered okra
directions: Wash and slice okra thin.
Put in large stainless steel pot that you have already poured cooking oil into.
Add tomato sauce and salt; cook on low fire, stirring often.
Cover pot between stirrings.
Cook on low fire about 45 minutes, stirring often.

title: english pot roast(crock pot)
directions: Place onion and celery in bottom of pot. Put the roast on top of these. Put salt, pepper and vinegar on the meat and add bay leaf and 5 cups water. Cook 5 to 7 hours. Remove meat. Add cabbage and cook on
high until cabbage is done.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Place rest of ingredients, except biscuits, with hamburger.
Pour in baking dish.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Place biscuits on top and bake until biscuits are done, about 20 minutes.

title: new jersey fried chicken
directions: Wash and drain chicken.
Mix all dry ingredients together in bag and shake.
Pour oil in deep frying pan and heat to very hot. Put chicken in bag and coat well.
Place in hot oil.
Put in butter; cover and let fry until golden brown and tender.
Serve with rice and vegetable.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt butter; add flour and cook for 1 minute.
Add paprika, mustard, chili powder, catsup, pepper sauce and cumin.
Stir well. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly to keep from sticking.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Tang, pudding and pineapple chunks together.
Cut all other fruits into bite size pieces.
Refrigerate all fruits, except bananas, overnight before using.
Make this 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Yields 36 cups.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Do not use mixer.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Cool in pan.
Makes 2 loaves, 9 x 4-inch.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring and combine with vanilla, salt and buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to sugar and shortening mixture.
Mix soda with vinegar and fold into batter.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in two 9-inch pans, well-greased and floured.
Stand full 10 minutes before turning out.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking pan.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice krispie cheesees
directions: Cream the oleo and cheese. Stir in dry ingredients. Add the Rice Krispies and roll in small balls (like marbles).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix and grind 50 Ritz crackers, 4 tablespoons sugar, walnuts and melted margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Saute pepper and onion in margarine until golden.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a 2 1/2-quart casserole for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Before serving, toss in nuts.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together marshmallow cream and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add cherries and juice and beat another 1 or 2 minutes.
Cover and chill overnight or 3 to 4 hours.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Use
your
usual
recipe
for cornbread; add the cream-style corn.
Put 1/2 the cornbread into a hot, greased baking pan. Cover
with
ground
beef,
cheese,
onions and peppers. Cover with remaining cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O.
Dissolve completely.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares or into shapes with cookie cutters.
Dip pan in warm water for 15 seconds to make removing easier.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon, drain and crumble.
Add onion to bacon fat and cook until lightly browned.
Place TV scalloped potato slices in a 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle mix over potatoes.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 30 to 35 minutes until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Carefully stir in bacon, onion, vinegar and bacon drippings and chopped egg. Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: megan's monkey bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together in bowl.
Cut biscuits up in quarters with scissors and lay on wax paper.
Drop 3 to 4 biscuits at a time in bowl and shake well.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Blend butter and sugar until creamy.
Mix in vanilla, pecans, and flour.
Roll into size of walnuts.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Roll 1st four ingredients into balls and place on a baking tray.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Melt jelly and mustard in a saucepan.
Pour over meatballs.
Serve warm.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: double banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Beat eggs in a small bowl.
Stir in bananas, water and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened; stir in cereal.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and remove from loaf pan.

title: schnitzel
directions: *Schnitzel is a cutlet, usually veal but other types of meat may be used.

title: pickle from kosher dill
directions: Drain Kosher Dill pickle.
Cut pickle round not too small (thin).
Put in same jar.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Put cloves in thin cloth and put in jar with pickle.
Add garlic.
Pour sugar mixture over pickle.
Put pickle in refrigerator jar upside down to dissolve sugar.
Shake often.
When sugar is dissolved pickle is ready to eat 24 hrs.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter cookies(healthful eating)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Combine peanut butter and sugar; fold in egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto Teflon baking sheets.
Flatten slightly with prongs of fork.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Mix well in blender.
Must be refrigerated.

title: swiss steak
directions: Heat oil in pan. Flour steaks and brown. Add about 1/2 c. or more of water. Cover and simmer 40-45 minutes until tender, turning once in a while. Make gravy from leftover drippings, (removing excess fat).
Add water as needed while cooking.

title: oven omelet
directions: Butter pie pan and arrange cheese slices on bottom.
Top with any additional filling.
Beat eggs and milk with fork.
Pour over cheese; bake at 325° for 40 minutes or less, if preferred.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and vanilla; beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix until blended. Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: fruit cake bars
directions: Cut butter into 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sift next 3 ingredients together.
Add slightly beaten eggs with sugar to flour mixture.
Fold in nuts and fruits.
Pour on baked crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm. Sprinkle powdered sugar on the top.

title: siberian sauce
directions: Melt butter, add flour, blend and gradually add the beef stock.
Stir in seasoning, chives, mustard and horseradish.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Strain.
Add cream and lemon juice and bring to a boil.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces and flour.
Brown in oil with onion.
Pour off oil and add tomatoes, juice and gravy mix.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: pita bread
directions: Dissolve yeast
and
honey in water for 5 minutes.
Add flour and
salt.
Knead until smooth, adding flour, if needed. Cut into 24
balls.
Knead each ball smooth and round.
Cover and rise 1 hour.

title: easy sour cream coconut cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add dry ingredients with cream.
Add vanilla and coconut last.
Grease and flour large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. This makes a large cake.

title: onion rye(bread machine bread)
directions: Select light crust setting.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo, water, eggs and mandarin oranges together well.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350°; let cool. Mix well the Cool Whip, pudding mix and pineapple.
Frost the cake and keep in cool place.

title: barbecue
directions: Bake meat in 325° oven for 5 hours.
Cool; then chop meat. Simmer for 1 hour the remaining ingredients.
Add to meat and mix well.
This freezes well.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Heat milk in saucepan.
In small bowl, mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Stir in enough milk to make a smooth paste.
Pour into warm milk.
Cook and stir continuously over moderate heat until sauce thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.
Serves about 4 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water with onion, salt, pepper and butter. Cook about 25 minutes or until done. Add cheese, egg, milk and bread pieces. Put in buttered baking dish. Top with bread pieces. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rosie's pesto
directions: Put the basil, garlic, pine nuts and Parmesan cheese in a blender or food processor.
Drizzle in the lemon juice while processing; continue to puree until a smooth paste.
Makes 3/4 cup Pesto.
Use only a small amount to coat pasta.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put basil, garlic, pine nuts and Parmesan cheese in food processor or blender.
Turn machine on and drizzle in lemon juice or olive oil.
Continue to puree until a smooth paste is formed. This sauce is delicious to spoon on top of broiled salmon steaks.

title: lemon bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together egg, milk, cooking oil and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, lemon peel and salt.
Add to egg mixture just until moistened.
Pour into a greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan onto wire rack.
Cool completely.
Wrap and store overnight in refrigerator.

title: spinach casserole
directions: To the beaten eggs, add the other ingredients one at a time, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put some extra grated cheese on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine, pour in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour into melted margarine. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: hot cranberry casserole
directions: Place apples and cranberries in 2-quart greased casserole. Sprinkle with lemon juice and cover with sugar in medium bowl. Toss together.
Blend oats, nuts, brown sugar and melted butter. Cover fruit with mixture.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quickie hawaiian pork(stove top)
directions: Combine meat, pineapple with juice, vinegar and ginger. Simmer one hour, covered.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Place rice in greased casserole with chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Mix celery soup and 2 cans water.
Pour over the mixture.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken salad crescent ring
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients, except rolls and half the cheese. Place the rolls on a round pan with the wide ends together and extending the tops outwards.

title: pickle roll-ups
directions: Cream mayonnaise, cheese, onion and garlic salt.
Spread on bread.
Wrap around pickle (cut off ends of pickles).
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice.
Electric knife works great!

title: chicken wings
directions: Soak wings in salt water for 1 hour; drain and put rest of ingredients (mixed) over wings.
Marinate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add can of Ro-Tel and cubed Velveeta cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Spread plain tortilla corn chips out on cookie sheet and drizzle with hot mixture when serving several people.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together ingredients. Form into large patties and roll lightly in flour.
Brown both sides in hot oil.
Pour soup and one can of water over meat patties. Simmer covered for 45 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 steaks.

title: brunch puffs
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water, butter and salt to a boil. Add flour all at once and stir until a smooth ball forms.
Remove from the heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls
2 in. apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 35 minutes or until golden brown. Transfer to a wire rack.
Immediately split puffs open; remove and discard tops and soft dough from inside.
Set aside.
Prepare filling.

title: special party dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese and carnation until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Serve with chips or Bugles.

title: special k bars
directions: In a large saucepan, melt sugar, Karo and butter.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add Special K and mix well.
Melt chocolate chips and put on top.

title: puffy eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook in boiling water 7 to 10 minutes. Drain and season with salt, pepper and onion juice.
Mix all ingredients using only half of cracker crumbs.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Put remaining crumbs on top.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rice custard
directions: Cook rice in water until well done. Combine all ingredients, except nutmeg, in casserole and sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done. It is done when knife is inserted and comes out clean.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let set overnight. Next day, bring to boil and cook until soft. Add gelatin and Kool-Aid, stirring until dissolved. May be canned or sealed with lid or paraffin.

title: balinese chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients with the dressing.
Chill for several hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Dissolve cream cheese in soup (mix well with mixer).
Add gelatine.
Cool.
Add all other ingredients. Put in oiled ring mold.
Serve with white club crackers.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter; mixing until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla.
Shape in balls, dip in sugar, and slightly flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Cut, peel and slice apples.
Place in dish.
Crumble sugar, flour and margarine together.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: healthy meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients. Spread evenly in pan.
Bake about 1 hour or until no longer pink in center.
Drain immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: smoked sausage bake
directions: Mix together all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover bottom with 1-inch of water.
Cover and bake until potatoes are done.

title: low-fat angel food strawberry delight
directions: Bake angel food cake as directed; cool.
Slice in half to make 2 layers.
Drain frozen strawberries.
Mix strawberries with glaze. Spread half of mixture between layers.
Put top layer of cake back on.
Spread other half of mixture on top.
Ice whole cake with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Stir eggs and sugar well.
Add margarine and stir to mix.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Bake in 9-inch unbaked pie crust for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt thelma's coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
You can add 1/2 cup crushed pineapple; makes it even better.

title: southern sweet potato souffle
directions: Whip all the ingredients until very fluffy.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: banana-nut loaf
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; set aside.
In mixing bowl thoroughly stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl cream the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and orange peel; beat well.
In a small bowl mash bananas with fork (should have about 1 cup).
Stir in milk.
Add flour mixture and banana mixture alternately to creamed
mixture.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Turn over pan and cool loaf on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chow chow
directions: Make a juice of sugar, vinegar, water. salt and turmeric.
Pour over vegetables.
Add sweet pickles and mix well.
Pour into jars. Heat in canner for 10 to 15 minutes to seal.
You can double the juice recipe if you would like.

title: speckled banana cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum and check quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now, go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cups, etc., and check that rum for quality again.
It must be just right.
Try it again.

title: noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll thin.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips. Let dry for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: one day sweet pickle slices
directions: Do not peel.
Do not cook.
Combine cucumbers and onion. Sprinkle with salt and let stand 2 hours.
Drain off.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add whole allspice.
Do not heat.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 1 day.
Ready to eat or can.
Keep in refrigerator up to 1 year.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Thoroughly add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. Mix flour and soda together.
Alternate flour and sour cream to butter and sugar.
Flour and butter a 12 cup tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add baking soda, sour cream and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour and mix well. Repeat three times.
Beat well.
Pour batter into large greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing according to directions. Add vegetables and seasoning.
Prepare soup, milk and parsley.

title: scalloped corn and broccoli
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add the remaining ingredients except butter and paprika.
Pour into greased or buttered casserole dish.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: tropical fruit punch(for diabetics)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Serve over ice.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with the chopped onion and drain fat; add taco seasoning to ground beef.
Pour mixture in a large saucepan and add the remaining ingredients (undrained).
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour taco soup over individual servings of tortilla chips.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Peel, clean and cook shrimp as for shrimp cocktail.
Mix soup and cheese over medium heat until well blended.
Chop seafood and add to mixture with mayonnaise.
Grate onion over pot so juice goes in.
In another pot dissolve gelatine with water until clear.
Add gelatine and sherry with pinch of salt to mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased mold.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
(Town House crackers go well with this.)

title: hobo bread
directions: Soak raisins, hot water and soda overnight.
Then add sugar, salt, oil and flour.
Bake in 1-pound coffee can.
Fill 1/2 full. Be sure can has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let set 5 to 10 minutes before removing from can.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large 8-quart pot cook ground beef and onions.
Add potatoes, carrots and water.
Then add beef bouillon, canned tomatoes and add V-8 juice.
Cook until tender.
Then add mixed vegetables.
Put any season you want.

title: winter cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrot, onion and green pepper.
In a small pan, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil over high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves, continue boiling for 2 minutes. Pour hot dressing over cabbage mixture and mix lightly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: reese's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 2 sticks butter with 1/2 cup cocoa and 1 cup water in saucepan; melt together over low heat.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk; add 2 eggs to saucepan and mix.
Mix in a bowl the flour, sugar, soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add to saucepan. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or muffin cups.
Pour in saucepan mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Let cake cool.
Mix peanut butter and spread on cool cake.
Mix 1 teaspoon vanilla with powdered sugar and dust top of cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; except coconut or nuts.
Then pour in coconut or nuts.
Mix well and pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grandma's meal in one!
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Mix with meat.

Add the peas, carrots, tomatoes, water and mushroom soup. Mix well and pour into a greased 3-quart or larger baking dish. Spoon mashed potatoes to cover top, then sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°, until brown.
This can be fixed the day before and cooked when needed.
This dish with salad and drink makes a good Sunday dinner.

title: 20-minute chicken parmesan
directions: Using palm of hand, flatten chicken to even thickness.
Dip chicken into egg then into crumbs to coat.
In skillet, (medium heat) melt butter, brown chicken on both sides.
Add sauce. Reduce heat.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses and parsley, cover and let simmer for 5 more minutes until cheese melts.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Cover and boil strawberries and vinegar for 2 minutes.
Add sugar and boil for 20 minutes.
Put in pans to cool.
Jars can be sealed or put in deep freeze not sealed.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time. Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Grease pan and line bottom with wax paper. Bake at 300° for 95 minutes.
Do not open oven until cake has baked for at least 80 minutes.

title: cherry pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Combine all the ingredients well and fill the baked pie shells.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core the cabbage; put in large pot of boiling water to separate leaves.
Trim off the hard vein.
Mix together the other ingredients.
Roll small part of meat mixture in leaf, starting at bottom of leaf.
Place in a baking dish.
Use 1 can tomatoes or tomato paste diluted with water to pour over rolls.
Place extra leaves of cabbage on top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Add a little water if needed during the cooking.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in large, plastic bag, using a rolling pin or use a food processor or blender and pulverize five at a time.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies without flour
directions: Combine beaten eggs, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla. Roll into walnut size balls and bake on ungreased sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop the 2 cups of popcorn according to directions.
Take a large brown grocery bag and spray the inside with Pam.
Put the popped corn in the bag.
Bring to boil the sugar, oleo, syrup and salt.
Boil for a full 2 minutes on High, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour mixture into bag and stir into the popcorn.
Fold bag down and shake.
Put bag into microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out and shake then return it to the microwave for another 1 1/2 minutes.

title: tomato aspic stagecoach inn
directions: Pour first 9 ingredients in pan and simmer for a long time; do not boil.
In a large pan, put remaining ingredients and mix well. Then strain hot mixture into cold, stirring constantly.
Pour into tray and sprinkle with finely minced onion.

title: shrimp-cucumber salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together cream cheese, mayonnaise or salad dressing, catsup, mustard and garlic powder. Stir in shrimp, cucumber and onion. Spread mixture over Melba toast, crackers or dip bread. Makes 1 1/4 cups of spread (20 servings).

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs on all sides.
Brown onion in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 15 minutes or until flavors are blended.
Pour sauce over browned ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: louise's grits casserole(breakfast dish)
directions: Cook together water, salt and grits.
Add garlic cheese and margarine.
Add egg/milk mixture to grits/cheese/margarine mixture.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small flowerets. Slice red onion thinly and separate into rings. Mix with blonde raisins. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together. Mix with broccoli mixture. Crush bacon and sprinkle on top of salad. Chill at least one hour. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt/brown pork chops.
Spray dish with Pam and layer chops, potatoes and onions.
Season each layer.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over casserole and bake in preheated 350° oven about 1 hour.
Also cooks very well in electric skillet.
Love those one pan dishes!

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 6 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Pour contents of both cans of soup in an oven bake casserole dish.
Add rice which has been cooked, corn and the chicken, cut up in pieces.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan.
Spread seeds out.
Sprinkle with salt.
Roast in oven 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: grandma's fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and evaporated milk and boil 6 minutes.
Put in large bowl.
Pour boiling syrup over remaining ingredients in bowl.
Beat until melted and pour into a buttered pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in metal box.

title: cheese ball
directions: This creamy cheese ball is a quick and easy treat for holiday parties.

title: chocolate cherry cake(quick and easy)
directions: Stir above with spoon.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost if you prefer.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain peaches; cut into bite size pieces.
Add yogurt, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle dry jello in and stir well. Ready to eat.

title: caramel coconut pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Add coconut and nuts.
Cook and stir until golden brown.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese and milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix soup and cheese together in microwave.
Drain Veg-All and asparagus.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup and cheese and pour over Veg-All and asparagus.
Top with crackers that have been mixed with melted margarine.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwich salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water, then set in hot water. Mix with mayonnaise and other ingredients.
Use as a spread for fancy sandwiches on white or brown bread.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, 1/2 stick margarine, milk and vanilla.
Spoon into a 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter until light; blend in molasses. Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.

title: cornmeal waffles
directions: In medium bowl lightly beat egg substitute.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add corn muffin mix, onion powder, thyme and black pepper. Blend until batter is slightly lumpy.
Preheat waffle iron.
Pour about 1 cup batter onto hot iron; cook waffles until crisp and golden.
If desired, place in 300° oven to keep warm.

title: delicious garden salad with zesty salad dressing
directions: Place salad greens on 4 salad plates.
Arrange sliced celery, shredded carrots, mandarin oranges and sliced almonds over greens. Drizzle with Zesty Salad Dressing.

title: what's for dessert pie?
directions: Beat eggs well and add all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Rub casserole with margarine.
Cover bottom of casserole with layer of broken saltines, next a layer of asparagus (1/2 can), a layer of soup (1/2 can) and a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat with saltines, asparagus, soup and end with cheese.
Pour juice from asparagus over this.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts and browns.

title: sherry's homemade butter
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Recipe will be double when finished.

title: squash casserole(for 6 people)
directions: Mix well. Add 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder when ready to bake. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients and press with a fork into the bottom of a spring form pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together.
Roll in chopped nuts and chill.

title: chocolate town pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In small mixer bowl, cream butter; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans (and Kahlua); pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool about 1 hour; serve warm with scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: caramel corn
directions: Remove all unpopped kernels and place popcorn in a deep dish baking pan.
Take other ingredients, mix together and bring to a soft-ball consistency.
Pour liquid over popcorn and stir.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Remove and stir. If it is very gooey, leave for 5 more minutes.
Remove from oven and pour onto buttered wax paper.
Let cool and then enjoy!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions and cut in half.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook a skillet of corn bread according to directions, except add fewer eggs.
Bake.
Crumble corn bread.
Toast 4 pieces of light bread in corn bread.
Cook the celery and onion in chicken broth until tender.
Pour mixture in corn bread; mix with a fork until moist (not wet).
Add the sage and black pepper.
Eat as is, or bake and eat with chicken gravy.

title: grandaddy's strawberry cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 400° in 3- 9 inch cake pans. Let cool.

title: ranch style chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cool and debone and chop into bite size pieces. Add in layers mushroom soup, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 of cheese, onions and cover with chips.
Sprinkle chili powder over all, then chicken broth.
Next, layer chicken soup, cheese, onions, chips and top with Ro-Tel tomatoes (chopped) and remaining cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 quarts.
Best when served hot.
Can make ahead.

title: mayonnaise sandwich
directions: Spread mayonnaise on each slice of bread. (Be sure not to put too much mayonnaise.)
Put slices together and eat.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine starter, water and flour. Let stand overnight. Next day, add shortening, sugar, salt and 1/2 to 1 teaspoon soda, depending on sourness of starter. Stir until well blended. Turn out on well floured surface. Knead thoroughly, adding more flour as needed. Divide dough and make into loaves. Put into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans. Let rise until double in size, as long as 3 hours. It rises slower than regular bread. Brush with butter. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: keynote fried shrimp
directions: Shell and devein shrimp; dry on toweling.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, eggs and milk in mixing bowl; beat vigorously.
Dip shrimp into batter; fry in deep, hot oil until golden brown.

title: chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: In medium skillet, melt margarine.
Add chicken and brown on both sides 12 to 16 minutes.
Add mushrooms, wine and basil. Cook, covered, over low heat 5 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cook bacon.
Cook onion in butter until soft, then blend in flour and salt.
Add sour cream gradually to flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Heat to boil and add corn.
Bring to a boil again and fold in 1/2 cup crumbled bacon or 1/2 jar bacon pieces. Turn into greased baking dish and garnish with remaining crumbled bacon and parsley.

title: sweet and pungent meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in the crock-pot.
Stir well! Cover and cook on: low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 to 6 hours. Makes about 5 quarts.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and fruit cocktail and add to sugar and flour mixture.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: caramel apple bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch square baking pan. In medium-size bowl, combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup brown sugar. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Transfer mixture to pan and press in an even layer in bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: golden blend au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Thaw vegetables under cool tap water. Drain.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Stir in flour and onion salt. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Place vegetables in cheese sauce.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Cheese may be omitted to obtain a cream sauce.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and pepper; shape firmly into 6 patties.
In skillet, brown patties; pour off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and water.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Follow cake instructions except where it calls for water. Substitute mandarin orange juice and then add water to equal what the recipe called for.
After cake is mixed well, add oranges and pour into 13 x 9 x 2 inch greased pan.
When cake is done, let it cool well then pour topping over.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients (except oats).
Heat to full, rolling boil.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in oats and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: beef casserole
directions: Place a plastic colander in a large glass mixing bowl. Crumble ground round into small pieces and cover with wax paper. Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring after 2 1/2 minutes.
In a 3-quart casserole, combine ground beef, celery, onion, tomatoes, rice, chili powder, pepper and mushrooms.
Microwave covered on High setting for 10 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Stir well.
Reduce power level to Medium (50% power), and microwave covered for 20 minutes or until rice is soft.
Serves 4.

title: whipped cocoa cream frosting
directions: Beat on a low speed to blend.
Beat on medium speed until stiff peaks form.

title: spaghetti with pesto and clams
directions: Chop mushrooms and saute with 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large frying pan; set aside.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.
In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with condensed milk, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter chips, stir just enough to distribute chips evenly in mixture.
Spread into prepared pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan, peel off foil and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Mix together well.
Add dry ingredients and sour milk alternately.
Stir in mashed bananas and nutmeats.
Put into 2 greased regular sized loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, soup and milk; heat on low until everything is melted and smooth.
In casserole dish, layer broccoli, Fri Chik and soup mixture until all ingredients are used.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
During last 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle with bread crumbs and grated cheese.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and pour over chicken. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: glazed pork roast
directions: Score fat on roast in a diamond design.
Rub salt and pepper into scored slits and over entire surface of roast.
Place roast, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of roast, making sure it does not touch fat or bone.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: taco-chip dip
directions: Spread beans in a rectangular cake pan.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco mix together, then spread over beans.
Chop onions and sprinkle on top.
Place chopped tomatoes over onions and olives over tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Can be made 1 to 2 days ahead.
Serve with taco chips.

title: black-eyed peas with bacon
directions: Place peas, beans and enough water to cover in a large kettle; bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Do not drain.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
salt
and	margarine or butter.
Stir well. Add eggs, mix well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well and
pour
into
unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour, checking for doneness.

title: stir fry steak or beef(yield: 4 or more servings)
directions: (We also use Mandarin Marinade - found in Asian aisle of Stop & Shop.)

title: dilled peas
directions: Cook peas and onion, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp-tender (or cook frozen peas and onion according to peas package directions).
Drain well. Stir in margarine, dill weed, salt and pepper.
Heat through.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in the top of a double boiler.
Fold in the chow mein or corn flakes, then marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased waxed paper. Cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: frankfurter pie
directions: Mix potatoes, carrots, onions, catsup and 1 1/3 cups of water; cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 25 minutes.

title: jailhouse rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water; set aside.
Combine potatoes, oleo, eggs, salt and sugar.
Blend into flour.
Add yeast water; mix thoroughly.
Place in greased bowl, cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll out like biscuits, cut out and place 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Butter tops and let stand for several hours.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: paprikas csirke
directions: In
a
Dutch
oven,
saute onions until translucent, in margarine.
Remove
onions with a slotted spoon and set aside. In remaining
pan
juices,
brown
chicken
well on all sides. Return onions to pan, stir in the paprika, half of the peppers and half of
the
tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Turn chicken;
add mushrooms and cook, covered, until chicken is tender
(approximately 10 to 15 minutes). Transfer chicken to serving
dish
and
keep
warm.
Stir sour cream into Dutch oven; add
a
little water if necessary to make pan gravy. Add additional
seasoning,
if
necessary,
and pour over chicken. Garnish with remaining tomatoes and pepper slices.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco beef noodle bake casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown beef and onion; stir in sauce, water and seasoning mix.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, flour, Mozzarella cheese and bouillon cube; mix well.
Add noodles, green onions and green pepper.
Blend well.
Spoon mixture into well-greased 2-quart dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake 2 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies with rolling pin in a Ziploc bag or by using a food processor.
In a medium size bowl, beat pudding mix and milk with wire whisk or on medium speed with a mixer for 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and 1/3 of the crushed cookies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper, 1 teaspoon at a time.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Put all in saucepan and heat over medium heat until cheese has melted and soup is hot.

title: sour cream horseradish sauce
directions: Fold horseradish and parsley into sour cream.
Serve with roast beef or prime rib.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Put on buns and wrap in foil, 2 at a time in a single layer.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until warmed.

title: surprise roll-ups
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Cut crusts off bread and roll flat with rolling pan. Spread cream cheese mixture over bread and roll up like jelly roll.
Dip in 1 stick melted butter, then in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Can be cut in half.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg, then pineapple. Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Nuts and coconut may be added.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwich
directions: Mix Hidden Valley Ranch and cream cheese.
Spread on cocktail bread and put on slice of cucumber.
Sprinkle with salad seasoning.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add the next 5 ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling water.
While noodles are cooking, mix the cream cheese, sour cream and chopped onions. After meat and noodles are cooked, mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour, dash of salt and melted butter.
Pour over pecans in unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes or until knife inserted in pie comes out clean.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Boil crawfish and shell.
Cook noodles for five minutes.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6 to 8. Serve with vegetables and salad.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Place all vegetables in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth. Pour over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced punch
directions: Combine water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon; boil ten minutes. Add orange juice and lemonade (undiluted).
Reheat and serve hot.

title: naked apple pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, brown sugar, egg, vanilla and pinch of salt.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Mix both mixtures together.
Add the apples and nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool Whip or ice cream is good on top when you serve it.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in blender/processor to make a slush. Add dry champagne and strawberry seltzer.
Float strawberries, oranges.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter, sugar, peanut butter and Rice Krispies; form into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and put on waxed paper until chocolate is set.

title: pineapple right-side-up cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted pan.
In small saucepan, melt margarine; stir in brown sugar until well mixed.
Press brown sugar mixture in bottom of prepared pan.
Cut pineapple slices in half; place 6 halves on top of the brown sugar to form a ring.
Cut each of the remaining pineapple halves into 3 pieces.
Place 1 piece between each pineapple half.
Place cherry in center of each pineapple half.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese and sausage get softened.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Store in airtight tin.
Best if served same day.

title: crab cakes
directions: Blend all ingredients except crab.
Add crab meat and toss gently.
Mold into cakes and fry in butter until browned.
Makes 8 to 10 cakes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line a well-greased pizza pan with the cookie dough.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Let cool.
Whip cream.
Mix sugar, vanilla and cream cheese and fold in whipped cream.
Spread mixture over cookie dough.
Layer over the top: pineapple, bananas, strawberries and pecans.

title: pink clover salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add salt; chill until it thickens, then add pineapple (juice and all), whipped cream and rice.
Chill before serving.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Use one cup milk.
Add corn, beans, soup and dill seed to macaroni and cheese.
Place French fried onions on top.

title: pilgrim pumpkin pie
directions: Refrigerate pie shell.
Heat oven to 425°.
Combine sugar, salt and spices.
Add pumpkin, milk, and eggs.
Heat until smooth. Pour into shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce the heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes or until the custard is set. Cool.

title: veggie pizza
directions: *Cut veggies small; use 1 cup of 6 kinds of veggies.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter.
Add mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with grated cheese.

title: fruit bars
directions: Boil raisins and 2 cups water; drain.
Then add 1 1/2 cups cold water to raisins and set aside.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco.
Add sugar; cream well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 375° until brown (10 to 12 minutes).
Remove from cookie sheet and let cool on wax paper.
Makes a large quantity (6 to 7 dozen).
These cookies freeze well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Blend soup, mayo, mushrooms and onions together.
Place broccoli on bottom of baking dish.
Spread soup mixture over broccoli.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: savory meat loaf with oven roasted potatoes
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, 1/2 can onions, egg and Worcestershire thoroughly.
In baking pan, shape firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf. Place potatoes around meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir potatoes.
Spoon remaining soup over meat loaf.
Bake 25 minutes or until meat loaf is done.
Stir potatoes.
Sprinkle remaining onions over meat loaf.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden. Serves 8.

title: poppy seed noodles
directions: Combine noodles, poppy seed, almonds, butter and rinds.
Toss together lightly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Turn into buttered casserole and top with sour cream.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: jerome cookies
directions: Layer row of graham crackers in glass pan (9 x 13-inch); makes 2 1/2 rows.
In saucepan, melt the margarine.
Add sugar, egg and milk.
Stir constantly over medium-high until it boils.
Take off and add the coconut, pecans and graham cracker crumbs.
Stir until mixed.
Pour over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Pat down.

title: gorgonzola chicken breasts with port wine
directions: Place chicken breasts on flat surface.
With sharp knife parallel to surface and beginning at curved edge of chicken breast, cut each lengthwise to within 1/4-inch of opposite edge.
Open each piece out flat and sprinkle 2 tablespoons cheese over one-half. Fold second half over cheese and press edges to close.
Dip chicken in egg, then flour that has been seasoned to taste.
Then finally in bread crumbs to coat lightly.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Fry hamburg; drain fat.
Mix all together.
For smaller portion, cut measurements in half.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix last eight ingredients and pour over raw broccoli. Marinate for 24 hours; place in Tupperware bowl to marinate and turn bowl over once in a while.
(Make sure tops on securely before this.)
Serve cold.

title: tasty crust for fried pies
directions: Mix the flour, shortening and salt, then add buttermilk and egg white.
Beat until stiff.
Chill before using.
(Can be kept in refrigerator until used.)
Fill with filling of your choice. This is the best crust!!

title: american-indian fry bread
directions: For smaller portions, recipe may be cut in half.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook
vermicelli according to directions and drain.
In bowl place
chopped celery, bell pepper, onions, tomatoes and drained pimento.
Add
vermicelli
to
vegetables.
Add lemon juice, Accent, salt, pepper and olive oil.
Toss all ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise
(I
do
not use the full pint) according to taste.
Refrigerate
until
ready
to serve.
The longer it is in the refrigerator the better it tastes.

title: chocolate oat squares
directions: Cream

butter and brown sugar. Beat in eggs and 2 tsp. vanilla. Combine oats, flour, 1 tsp. salt and baking soda, stir into creamed mixture. Press 2/3 of oat mixture into greased 15x10 inch baking pan. In a pan, combine milk, chips and remaining butter and salt. Cook and stir over low heat until chocolate is melted. Remove from the heat, stir in walnuts and remaining vanilla. Spread over crust. Sprinkle with remaining mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: westhaven cake
directions: Mix all together dates, hot water and baking soda and let cool.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, then mix dry ingredients together.
Then alternate dry and date mixture together, beating well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.
You can sprinkle with a little powdered sugar when done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together well the zucchini, cooking oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, baking powder and nuts; add to preceding mixture.
Mix well. Divide into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: banana nut bread
