directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas and mix well.
Add rest of dry ingredients.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes depending on size of pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: rigatoni sauce
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add garlic, tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Boil 1/2 hour, stirring often.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and sweet basil.
Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Cool. Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped milk. Pour into dish lined with vanilla wafers or Graham Cracker Crust.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Soak raisins in eggs and vanilla for 1 hour.
Cream together butter and sugars until fluffy.
Mix flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda together.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Stir in raisins and oatmeal.

title: cranberry pineapple fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Chill and serve.
May be frozen for later use.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together rice, water and soup mix in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place chicken on top.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: johnson's temptation (swedish)
directions: Saut onions in 1 tablespoon butter. Butter baking dish. Layer potatoes, anchovies and onions, ending with top layer of potatoes. Pour the brine from the anchovy can on top. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Add half of the cream. Bake in 400° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Add remaining cream after 10 minutes of baking as needed. Serve hot from baking dish. Serves 4 to 6.

title: scampi (shrimp)
directions: Heat oil and seasonings; add shrimp.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes. Serve over rice or your favorite pasta.
The amount of shrimp used is optional.
Less is better if using fresh pasta.

title: party shrimp mold
directions: Place gelatine, Clamato juice and V-8 juice in a small pan; mix well and bring to a boil.
In a bowl, add rest of ingredients and mix well with a fork.
Add 6 drops of Tabasco sauce.
Pour in a well-oiled mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: oriental meat balls
directions: Soften Croutettes with 1 cup tomato sauce in 2-quart mixing bowl; let stand to soften.
Add beef, well-beaten egg, soy sauce and water chestnuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Gently form into meat balls.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Add water to remaining tomato sauce; pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
May be served over fluffy rice or long grain and wild rice.

title: yummy strawberry pie
directions: Make sauce by combining sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Stir the strawberry jello into the hot sauce.
Cool 1 hour.
Fill the baked pie shell with fresh berries (slice them if they are large).
Pour the sauce over the berries. Refrigerate.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind pork and ham together.
Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Shape and bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Combine vinegar, water, mustard, cloves and brown sugar.
Baste ham loaf when it is almost done.

title: mile high meringue
directions: Combine
2 tablespoons sugar, cornstarch and cold water in saucepan.
Stir
until cornstarch dissolves.
Cook mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat when mixture is thick and clear.
Cool.

title: all in one dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato juice well.
Spray dish with Pam and place loaf in pan.
Pour over tomato juice.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; reserve some cheese and cracker crumbs for top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: texas salad
directions: Heat pineapple and dissolve jello in pineapple; let set until partly congealed.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter oat bars
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Mix in soda.
Stir in oatmeal. Add chips, nuts or whatever you like.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Yield:
Many cookies or make a cookie sheet of bars.

title: quick cornbread
directions: Mix and bake as directed.
You may double the recipe for serving more people.
Serves 8 people.
Serves 16 if doubled.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix the jello, cornstarch and sugar together.
Add the water. Bring mixture to a boil.
Let cool until partially set; mix.
Pour over berries in cooked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: In a large electric skillet, melt butter.
Saute onion and bell pepper until tender, but firm.
Add the consomme soup (mixed with 2 cups water) and the white rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring every so often to avoid sticking.
It may be necessary to reduce heat.
(May also be placed in a large Pyrex bowl, after bell pepper and onion are sauteed, with all ingredients.)

title: skillet okra and rice
directions: Cook okra in small amount of oil until done. Cook ground beef until slightly brown. Add okra, seasonings, onion and water. Simmer until 30 minutes before steaming.
Add rice and enough water to steam rice. Cook until rice is tender.

title: viennese chicken
directions: Rinse chicken under cold water.
Place in baking pan and season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour. Remove and set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into bite-size pieces.
Fry in oil until done. Cook egg noodles; drain.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and milk and heat thoroughly.
Put meat in sauce; cook 5 minutes more. Pour over cooked noodles.

title: best ever hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Stirring until chocolate melts. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Beat with rotary beater until thick. Serve hot or cold. Great on ice cream.

title: french cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°, grease muffin pan.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in mixing bowl; set aside.
In another bowl beat egg; stir in butter and milk.
Add liquid ingredients all at once to flour mixture, stir only until flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a lightly greased 4-quart casserole dish; set aside.
Place butter in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt; cover and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove mixture from microwave; stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn; stir until all is coated.
Cook popcorn mixture on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring well after each minute.
Remove from oven; stir well.
Spread in a lightly buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; cool thoroughly.
Break into pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: jelly bean cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Beat in egg, baking soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats until blended.
Add jelly beans.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop rounded spoonfuls of batter about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: old fashion gingerbread
directions: Stir together in large bowl the brown sugar, oil and eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Roll out and cut or pinch into patties. Bake in greased pan at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
In bowl, prepare eggs, margarine, salt, muffin mix and onion.
Stir in cooked broccoli.
Bake in 8 x 11-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well. Combine flour, soda, salt and add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape dough into 48 (1-inch) balls.
Place in lightly greased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Shaping ball into shell. Bake at 350°
for 12 minutes.
Dough will rise during baking. Remove from oven and immediately push a miniature peanut butter cup evenly into each hot crust.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring tomato soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and Worcestershire sauce to a boil.
Pour over carrots (drained), onion and bell pepper.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in an iron skillet at 350° until brown.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla. Stir over low heat until chocolate and oleo melt. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute (220°). Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm. Stir in vanilla. Beat until smooth spreading consistency. Add 1 cup chopped nuts if desired.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer; blend well.
Combine oats, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls of dough, 2 inches apart, onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on cooling rack.

title: crab lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Heat shrimp soup and add crab.
Mix together cottage cheese, cream
cheese, egg, basil (salt and pepper) and onion.
Put a layer of noodles on bottom of baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture (part) over noodles, then some of the heated soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with sliced tomatoes. Bake 15 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Add shredded Cheddar and bake 30 more minutes until browned and bubbly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat; add melted butter, Karo, vanilla and 1 teaspoon of flour and beat.
Place pecans in unbaked pie crust.	Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in pan.
Add in dots of butter.
Cook in a 350° oven about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: great pound cake
directions: Have eggs and butter at room temperature.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar thoroughly.
Add one egg at a time beating each time until all five eggs are blended.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Add sifted flour and baking powder mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Put in cold water.
Turn oven to 350°.
Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.

title: rhubarb strawberry pie
directions: In a mixing bowl combine the first four ingredients and let stand for 15 minutes. Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Add filling.
Top with a lattice crust.
Flute the edges.
Brush with cream and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 400° or until the crust is golden and filling is bubbling.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tomato pork gravy
directions: Leave 1/4 cup stock in pan.
Blend flour and add water gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in tomato soup and season with salt and pepper.

title: quiche
directions: Place one half of the shredded cheeses on the two unbaked pastry crusts.
Spread the chopped onions on top of cheeses.
In bowl, beat together eggs, half and half, salt, pepper and garlic, until very fluffy.	Pour over the cheese.
Break butter into small pieces over top and sprinkle other half of the shredded cheeses on top.
Bake in preheated 425° oven 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.	Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings per quiche.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and beat. Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with salad oil. Add vanilla, carrots, nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan or bake 1 hour in an angel food cake pan.

title: sausage pasta supper
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Stir-fry mushrooms, onion and broccoli, sprinkled with garlic powder and oregano, until vegetables are cooked, yet still firm.
(Do not overcook.)

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix together; shape into small balls.

title: apples cooked in spices
directions: In medium skillet over medium heat, melt the butter until foaming.
Add apples, cook 2 minutes, tossing occasionally.
Add honey and sprinkle spices over apples.
Toss gently to combine. Cook until apples are tender, then serve while hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash.
Cover squash with water and cook 3 to 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix squash, soup, onion, carrots and sour cream.
Place in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Combine stuffing and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
At this point, casserole can be refrigerated and baked later.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best ever one minute fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Take off heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add butter, peanut butter, and vanilla.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix mushroom and French onion soup with 1 can water.
Add stew beef.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Peel and cut vegetables; add to meat mixture.
Bake for an additional 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix flour, sugars, soda, salt, butter, 1/3 cup peanut butter, egg, vanilla and oatmeal with a fork or mixer until particles are coarse crumbs.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle immediately with the chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread evenly.

title: apricot-stuffed pork chops
directions: Chop enough apricots to make 1/2 cup; reserve remaining apricot halves.
Make pockets in pork chops, cutting from rib side to fat edge of each chop (do not cut through fat edge).
Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat; brown pork chops on both sides. Set aside.
Combine rice, soup mix and water in a saucepan; cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes.
Add chopped apricots, pecans and mace, mixing well.
Spoon about 1/3 cup rice mixture into each pork chop pocket.
Place chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Combine apricot preserves, lemon juice and cloves.
Brush chops with mixture; bake, uncovered, an additional 15 minutes.
Transfer to a serving platter and garnish with reserved apricot halves.

title: peanut butter honey cookies(refrigerator cookie)
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, honey, peanut butter and egg thoroughly. Measure flour and blend dry ingredients. Stir into shortening mixture. Stir in nuts. Shape into a strip about 10 x 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch. Wrap in wax paper; store in the refrigerator for several hours. Bake as needed.

title: tuna steak stew
directions: In a 12-inch pan, saute garlic in oil.
Add onion and saute until translucent.
Add tomatoes, bay leaves, black pepper and paprika.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Add wine, potatoes and tuna. Cover and let simmer on low flame approximately 30 minutes. Serves 5.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, combine eggs, sugar, salt and juice.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Cool.
Add celery, pineapple, nuts and apples.
Fold in whipped cream and freeze. Place in refrigerator for about two hours before serving.
May be refrozen.
This keeps several months in freezer.

title: "like" kentucky chicken coating
directions: Coat chicken with mix.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.

title: dirt cake
directions: Bowl 1:
Mix cream cheese, margarine and Cool Whip.

title: frozen peanut butter delight
directions: In small bowl, combine sugar, crumbs and margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In small mixer bowl, beat powdered sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese at medium speed, scraping bowl often until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
At low speed, gradually beat in milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust. Sprinkle with peanuts.
Freeze 3 hours or until serving time. Makes 18 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 14 x 10 x 2-inch (approximately) cake pan that's greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: broccoli ham ring(brunch)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop ham, broccoli and onion with food chopper.
Finely snip parsley with Kitchen Cutters. Coarsely grate cheese with grater-slicer.
Mix all ingredients except crescent rolls and set aside.
Arrange crescent triangles in a circle on a 13-inch baking stone with bases overlapping in center and points to the outside.
There should be a 3-inch diameter circle in center.
Evenly spoon filling over base.
Fold points of triangle over filling and tuck underbase at center.
Filling will not be completely covered.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix together all other ingredients except cheddar cheese.
DO NOT DRAIN BROCCOLI!! Pour batter over butter.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown and tests done.

title: beef goulash
directions: Peel, dice and cook carrots until done.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add onion and celery to grease in Dutch oven and saute about 5 minutes.
Add broken up ground beef; brown.
Combine all ingredients to beef in Dutch oven.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until flavors are blended.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature, mix all ingredients well. Chill then form into a ball.
Roll in parsley and chopped nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Cut pita bread into 8 wedges and lightly toast.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, cumin and jalapeno pepper.
Spread each wedge with a dab of the mayonnaise mixture.
Top with half sliced tomato and 2 slices of your favorite ham.
Garnish with a slice of olive and a few sprouts.
Serve.

title: apricot (no bake) ball cookies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Roll in balls, then roll in coconut.

title: rice
directions: Mix together and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops and onions in oil.
Drain grease and remove chops.
Stir in remaining ingredients and add chops.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan, melt butter in water and bring to boil.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Add water and beat until smooth.
Add sour cream and almond extract.
Beat eggs and add to cake mixture.
Pour batter into a greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Frost cake while still warm.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water, lemon juice and pineapple with juice and sugar. Refrigerate until it begins to jell.
Tear half of angel food cake into small pieces and spread over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Whip 2 envelopes Dream Whip and fold into gelatine mixture. Pour over cake in pan.
Tear other half of cake into small pieces and spread over mixture in pan.
Press down lightly.
Whip remaining 2 envelopes Dream Whip and spread on top.
Cover with shredded coconut.
Chill overnight.
Serves 13 to 20.

title: stromboi sandwich
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
In large skillet, brown sausage with ground beef.
Add onions, green peppers and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes; stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic salt and rosemary.
Stir and mix well. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding; add marshmallows, Cool Whip, pecans and cherries.
Chill.
Serve.

title: mcholt's irish soda bread
directions: Stir the dry ingredients together.
Add raisins and coat them well.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk and butter. Add to flour mixture.

title: slush punch
directions: May use any flavor gelatin.
Dissolve jello in 5 cups boiling water.
Add all other ingredients.
Freeze.
Keeps well.
Set out of freezer 3 to 4 hours before serving (sometimes you have to chop with wooden spoon).
Add 6 quarts 7-Up and 2 quarts ginger ale when serving.
No need for ice or ice rings.
Stays cold.
Makes at least 150 punch cups.

title: banana pudding for a bunch
directions: Mix pudding and milk; mix in sour cream and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
In a very large bowl, put 1 layer of vanilla wafers, layer of pudding mixture and layer of bananas.
Repeat layers.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop all vegetables fine. Mix with salt and let stand 24 hours. Drain off brine. Squeeze vegetables and add other ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Add good vinegar to cover. Simmer for 1 hour, keeping covered closely. Pack into hot dry jars and seal. Makes approximately 14 half-pints.

title: quick and easy cheese pockets
directions: Roll out crescent rolls.
Tear on line 4 square sections, pushing other lines together.
Mix chicken, cream cheese and chives.
Spoon mixture in center of crescent squares.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Fold crescent square to form pockets.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Add nuts, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: banana treat(preschool snack)
directions: Cut banana into pieces easy for a child to get a fork into and also into their mouths!
Put some yogurt in a small bowl.
Put graham cracker crumbs in another bowl.
(Used T.V. dinner trays work great.)
Let child fork banana pieces, then dip into yogurt, crumbs and pop into mouth.
Be imaginative, coconut flakes, etc. may be substituted.

title: beef and noodle bake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix ground beef with tomato sauce and garlic salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Layer the beef mixture and noodle mixture until all is used.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in order given.
Sometimes I soak the fruit mix in brandy overnight...this is not necessary.

title: spice ornaments
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir in applesauce.
It will be thick.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter and lay on brown paper.
Let dry for 4 to 5 days, uncovered.
While wet, take a toothpick and cut hole for ribbon. Smaller cookie cutters work best.
Use spatula to place on brown paper.

title: butter brickle dessert
directions: Crush together graham and soda crackers; combine with brown sugar, margarine and nutmeats.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan and reserve 1 cup for the top.	Chill while preparing the filling.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and place in buttered casserole dish. Save broth.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and butter.
Pour over chicken soup mixture.
Pour 2 cups of chicken broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(Can be made the day before.
Just put in large dish and refrigerate.)

title: quick supper casserole
directions: Place crumbled hamburg in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle onion over hamburg; season with salt and pepper.
Spread mushroom soup over onion and hamburg; add 1/4 cup of water.
Sprinkle frozen Tater Tots on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown beef in
butter in 12-inch Dutch oven.
Add beans and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli stuffing
directions: Boil the broccoli and onion 5 minutes and then drain.
Add grated carrot, sour cream and soup.
Combine the 2 packages Stove Top stuffing with the melted butter.

title: bologna and cheese spread
directions: Grind bologna, cheese, onion, pepper and pickles in a bowl. Add other ingredients and mix well.

title: viennese pot roast
directions: Double a 5-foot length of foil.
Place on broiler pan.
Place roast on pan; brown under broiler.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Place 1/2 on bottom of roast and rest on top.
Seal foil; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until tender.

title: fruitcake cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into small muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mixed greens with cheese and green onion vinaigrette
directions: Heat walnut oil in heavy 6-inch skillet over medium-low heat. Add walnuts and cook until brown, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Combine with both lettuces and cheese in large bowl.
Just before serving, add vinaigrette and toss.

title: honey pears
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Peel and core pears so they have a hole right in the center or filling will run out.
In small bowl, combine honey, powdered ginger and walnuts.
Place pears in a shallow baking pan and spoon honey mixture into pears.
Bake 45 minutes or until pears are tender.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Sift flour.
Add soda and salt.
Sift with flour.
Beat egg until foamy in small bowl.
In large bowl, cream shortening.
Add sugars.
Beat well.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour mixture. Blend well.
Shape dough in balls, pressing with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chinese almond cookie
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg and almond extract.
Mix, knead until soft.
Form into little balls, flatten with hand.
The sign of the Chinese Almond Cookie is a red dot in the center of the cookie, which is made with red food coloring. Use a chopstick and dot it!

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat well the egg and egg yolk.
Cook egg, sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice in double boiler until thick.
When cool, pour over remaining ingredients.
Chill.
At Christmastime, add red and green cherries.

title: campfire hamburger meals
directions: You will need aluminum foil, 4 pieces, 12 x 12-inches.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Use 2 teaspoons of tea mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: grammie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cover raisins with hot water and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain and reserve the 6 tablespoons of liquid.
Cream sugar and shortening thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients. Mix with oatmeal and raisin liquid. Add fruits and nuts. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: biscuits
directions: Stir up and put in muffin tin.

title: mama's best giblet gravy
directions: Boil eggs for chipping up in gravy.
Peel and place aside.

title: daddy's forget-the-cookies-just-give-me-that-batter chocolate chip
directions: In a small pan, melt the butter.
While it's hot, add both sugars.
Let cool.
While the butter mixture is cooling, mix the flour, soda and salt in a bowl.
Beat the egg and add egg and vanilla to butter mixture.
Stir.
Add the butter mixture to the flour mixture.
Stir again, then add chocolate chips and nuts. Stir everything well and put into the fridge to cool for 1 hour.

title: mom's rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Line pan with half of the mixture. Add the rhubarb over the mixture.
In a saucepan, mix the water, sugar, salt, cornstarch and vanilla. Bring to a boil. Mixture will thicken.
Pour over rhubarb.
Sprinkle with remaining crust. Bake 1 hour in
a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Chop sausage into small chunks. After browning sausage, drain fat, reserving 3 tablespoons of fat. Add the flour; brown flour and fat.
Add drained sausage.
After mixture has been browned, gradually add milk; simmer until thickened.
Add pepper and sage while gravy is simmering.

title: rickie's cookies
directions: Mix sugar and margarine well.
Add eggs, flour and cream of tartar; mix well.
Then stir in pecans, candied fruit and cherries.
Roll in a long roll.
Wrap and chill overnight.
Slice about 1/8-inch thick.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: schawm tortes
directions: Beat egg whites stiff. Add sugar and salt. Fold in vanilla and pecans. Put brown paper on cookie sheet. Drop by spoonful. Bake at 275° for 45 minutes. Leave in oven until cool (may leave overnight). Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs with sugar.
Blend in butter.
Press firmly in bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.

title: butterscotch yule log
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water; remove from stove. Stir in condensed milk and vanilla.
Add chopped pecans; mix well. Chill until firm enough to handle.
Form into 12-inch roll on waxed paper.
Roll tightly in waxed paper to shape evenly.
Unroll and mark surface lengthwise with tines of fork; brush with egg white.
Press pecan halves into roll to completely cover surface. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices with sharp knife.
Makes 2 dozen slices (approximately).

title: chinese walnut chicken(stir-fry)
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Mix cornstarch, pepper, sugar, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken; stir to coat evenly.
Saute nuts until golden in 1 tablespoon oil. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Heat remaining oil.
Add chicken mixture; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add ham.
Stir in remaining soy sauce and broth, scraping up brown bits from bottom of pan.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Serve over rice.

title: onion patties
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix.
Add onion and stir to coat.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil or fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and 1 egg at a time. Add bananas. Beat. Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture slowly. Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer first five ingredients.
Add Colby cheese, bacon and hard-boiled eggs.
Make dressing.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine and chill.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: walnut angel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; stir in nuts. Drop from spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.
Can be used as is or ice according to taste.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In small bowl, stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture; stir until blended.

Pour batter onto grids of preheated lightly greased waffle iron (amount will vary according to size of waffle iron). Sprinkle a few chopped pecans on top of batter; close lid quickly; do not open during baking.
Remove cooked waffles and serve with maple syrup; fresh fruit and yogurt, etc.
Yields 12 waffles (4-inch squares).

title: cranberry chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine flour and baking soda.
Set aside.
In a bowl, beat sugars and butter.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add sugar mixture to dry ingredients and fold in chips, chopped cranberries and orange rind.
Drop dough on sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream sugar and cheese.
Mix in all other ingredients. Freeze, thaw for 30 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini and onion.
Mix with salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients and cook until they start to thicken (does not get very thick, only less runny).
Add vegetables, mix well and cook slowly 1/2 hour.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: tiny swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meats together, then bread crumbs and milk.
Stir to blend until a paste-like consistency.
Add to ground meat in large bowl. Add seasonings and blend mixture well.
Roll between hands into 1-inch balls.
Set on waxed paper to dry.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugars and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into 4 sections each. Roll in sugar mixture.
Pour nuts into Bundt pan.
Place covered biscuit pieces in pan.
Melt butter and add remaining sugar mixture.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove promptly from pan.

title: geri's dirty rice
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage, celery and garlic; drain grease. Add water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil; add rice, onion, file gumbo and Tony's.
Turn heat down and simmer with a lid for 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze the spinach until dry.
Stir in remaining ingredients, blending well.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Stir before serving.

title: clam chowder
directions: Rinse clams in strainer (reserving 1/2 cup juice).
Saute bacon until crisp; add onion until tender and drain.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: italian sausage bianco(sausage in white sauce)
directions: Pierce sausage with a kitchen fork and place in a lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Turn sausage and cook another 15 to 20 minutes until brown and remove off most of the fat contents.
Remove sausage and drain on paper towels.
Set aside.

title: grilled fish italiano
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, milk and Italian seasoning.
Place fish on greased grill over medium hot coals or rack of broiler pan; brush with remaining mayonnaise mixture.
Continue grilling or broiling 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: buddie's burger and tots casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle onion over meat.
Pour 1 can undiluted mushroom soup over mixture.
Cover top with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf men will eat
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand in large bowl except catsup. Shape a loaf by hand in ungreased rectangular pan.
Spread enough catsup over loaf to cover top.
Bake uncovered 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: savory cheese spread
directions: Puree cottage cheese in blender; add margarine.
Blend well. Add other ingredients.
Blend well.
Serve at room temperature. Yields 2 3/4 cups; 35 calories per serving.

title: baked crab imperial casserole
directions: Mix together green pepper, salt, mustard, pepper, egg and salad dressing.
Fold in crab meat.
Put in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour a thin coat of Old Bay seasoned bread crumbs on top of this.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 20 - 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and nutmeg together.
Combine buttermilk, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 350° until set in middle.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Combine molasses, shortening and boiling water, mix well with flour, soda and spices.
Blend well, let stand at least 2 hours or overnight.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick, cut and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into small pieces and mix with raisins, pecans, onions, water chestnuts and carrots.
Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make a dressing.
Pour over the broccoli mixture and toss well.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Refrigerate and marinate several hours before serving.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients except eggs in a saucepan.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour vinegar mixture over potatoes.
Add eggs and toss.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice the day before and refrigerate.
Heat oil in deep frying pan.
Saute meat and celery.
Add rice, stirring and press out any lumps.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Make a hollow in rice mixture and pour in beaten egg. Stir the pan until the egg begins to set.
Add onions and soy sauce.

title: peanut coated orange roughy
directions: Cut fillets into serving size pieces.
Combine peanuts and flour.
Dip fish into milk, then into flour mixture, coating well. Heat butter in pan.
Place fish in pan and cook for 6 to 8 minutes, turning once. (If using frozen fillets, allow an extra 3 minutes.)
Drain.
Serve immediately with salad or vegetable.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Brown bacon and round steak in skillet, stirring to brown all sides.
Add next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir in spaghetti and heat through.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: banana bars
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in bananas and egg.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate mini morsels.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan on rack.
Cut into bars or squares.
Well wrapped, these freeze well!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all except broccoli in bowl.
Add to broccoli in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onion, add tomato sauce and simmer for 30 minutes. Cook noodles and drain. Combine sour cream, green onions and cream cheese. Layer in ungreased casserole dish: noodles, meat, cream mixture ending with noodles on top. Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix flour, nuts, brown sugar and butter and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat eggs, confectioners sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Spoon into cooled crust; over that put layer of "well" drained crushed pineapple.
Top with bananas that have been dipped into pineapple juice.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts and cut-up maraschino cherries.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, salt and vanilla. Stir flour and pecans into the sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Chill at least an hour.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Place thumb gently in center of each ball.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool. Fill thumbprints with jelly or icing.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: moussaka
directions: Cook onion in butter with salt and pepper for 5 minutes.
Add meat and garlic; cook 10 minutes.
Add puree, water and nutmeg; cook 10 minutes.
Coat eggplant with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fry in hot oil.
Place 1/2 of eggplant in baking dish and cover with 1/2 meat mixture.
Repeat layers and top with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until hot.

title: clam bake
directions: Cover bottom of large pot with 1-inch of water.
Put in rack. Layer corn, chicken, potatoes, onions and celery.
Put sausage on top.
Cover with aluminum foil with holes punched in it.
Add clams.
Bring to full steaming boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in a bowl with a wooden spoon until creamy.
Mix in flour, oats, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by spoonful about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute and remove from pan.

title: good lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck in frying pan with minced garlic; salt and pepper.
Drain off any grease.
Add jar of Ragu and simmer. Meanwhile, cook noodles according to directions.
Do not overcook. Run cold water over noodles, so they won't stick.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix cottage cheese and egg together in separate bowl.
Layer lasagna beginning with noodles on bottom, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat. Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sherry cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening and mix.
Pour in half of the sherry and water. Beat well.
Add remaining sherry and eggs. Beat well. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Lightly sift powdered sugar over cake. Serves 12.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald 1/2 cup milk and 2 tablespoons Crisco.
Take off stove and add ice water.
Add yeast cake to warm water.
Mix with flour, salt and sugar, sifted together.
Make soft dough; roll out and let rise for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil in a large skillet for 8 to 10 minutes. Wipe up excess oil with paper towel.
Combine cumin and garlic with tomato sauce and pour over chicken, then add remaining ingredients. Cook and simmer, covered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook on high 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; drain juice from fruit and add enough water for 2 cups.
Add cheese while it's hot. Heat until dissolved, then add fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: easy cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Rub inside of small bowl with cut clove of garlic.
Blend cream cheese with seasonings.
Add clams which have been drained and chopped.
Add clam juice.
Put in a bowl and chill.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add milk alternately with flour to butter mixture.
Add nuts and cocoa.
Combine egg, soda and water; add to flour mixture.
Spread in a greased 10 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Cut roast into 1 or 2-inch cubes and put into crock-pot with 1 chopped onion and water. Cook on low overnight (10 to 12 hours). After cooking, drain off liquid. Remove all fat and bones. Break up the lean meat with fingers and return to pot with 1 chopped onion and barbecue sauce.
Cook on low for another 5 to 6 hours.

title: "a" quickie
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly, stirring occasionally to break it up.
While it is frying, combine corn and eggs (slightly beaten). Season with salt and green pepper.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Split rolls and spread margarine mix on both sides.
Put ham and cheese on bottom section of rolls and cover with top section.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Can freeze until heating time.

title: lemon angel food dessert
directions: Mix dry cake mix and pie filling together, pour into a 15 X 11-inch jellyroll pan that has been sprayed with Pam and floured very well.
Bake at 350° for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Cook sugar and Karo to good boil.
Immediately remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cornflakes and drop on wax paper.
Do not overcook.
It takes approximately 2 minutes.

title: fancy company chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Place chicken in bottom.
Lay a slice of cheese on each piece.
Layer mushrooms on top.
Mix soup and wine, pour over all.
Spread stuffing over soup.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a crust in a buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over this.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Roll pastry to fit 9-inch pie pan.
Brown beef and onion in a large skillet; cook until meat is brown.
Drain off drippings. Add potatoes, broth, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: kentucky bourbon balls
directions: In the mixing bowl of an electric mixer, beat the butter to soften, then gradually and thoroughly beat in the sugar and salt. Very slowly, so the mixture doesn't curdle, beat in the bourbon in a steady stream. Beat in the minced pecans and mix well. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours until firm.

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Cut tortillas into pieces. Spread pieces out on sheet; spray with Pam.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Check for browness.

title: sweet basil carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 1/8-inch slices or run through slicer of food processor.

Place them in vegetable steamer, covered, over boiling water for 10 minutes until tender, but not mushy. Remove from heat and set aside. Carrots may be steamed well in advance and combined with other ingredients immediately before serving.
In a large, heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add maple syrup, carrots, basil and salt.
Stir well to coat carrots thoroughly with butter sauce. Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Form patties and place in beaten egg, then in mixture formed by combining cornstarch and garlic powder.
Place patties in baking dish.
Mix together water, catsup, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Pour over patties and bake uncovered 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a 12 x 12 glass baking dish grease bottom then layer slices of bread on bottom- cut off all crust.
Put ham, cheddar cheese and chopped onion on top of bread.
In another bowl beat 4 eggs, add cream of mushroom soup, milk and mix together.
Pour over top - set in.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 layer torte
directions: Mix flour, oleo and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Press into 9 x13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Cream the cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1/3 of the Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust.
Combine pudding (instant) with milk.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Spread over creamed mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip; sprinkle with nuts, chocolate slivers and coconut.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake in shallow pan for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients in plastic bag or large bowl.
Mix well.
Bake on cookie sheet; stir often.
Cook for 40 minutes, until light brown and tender.

title: a good brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Line bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing edge to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat well and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and cut into squares.
Serve at once.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in container.
Put 2 teaspoons to a cup
of boiling water.
Stir with spoon, then drink.

title: mary lou's easy caesar salad
directions: Mix egg, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar, parsley, garlic, onion, mustard and celery salt in blender, then add anchovy paste and parsley flakes.
Then add Parmesan cheese.
If mixture is too thin, add another egg and more cheese to make thick and creamy. Put dressing in refrigerator to chill until ready to serve.

title: cheese scalloped corn casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Mix 2 tablespoons bacon drippings with 1/4 cup cracker crumbs; set aside for the topping.
Cook onion in remaining drippings until tender. Add remaining cup of cracker crumbs.
Mix and brown slightly. Combine onion crumb mixture with beaten eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in a shallow baking dish; sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Mix together zucchini, soda, butter and egg.
Sift flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt; stir in.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop batter by the teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: white fudge
directions: In large bowl, mix marshmallow cream, butter and chips; set aside.
In saucepan, cook sugar and milk on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil and continue boiling and stirring for 9 minutes.
Pour over ingredients in bowl; add vanilla.
Stir very well until creamy.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pans.
Makes 2 large Pyrex pans.

title: cheese-rice casserole(like a souffle)
directions: Melt oleo over medium heat.
Add flour and salt.
Stir until smooth and cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened and add cheese. Beat egg yolks until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/8 cup sauce to yolks and mix.
Then add into sauce and add rice and egg whites.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake over hot water at 325° for 1 hour.
May serve with tomato or cheese sauce.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Slice and clean mushrooms.
Put butter in a pan and bring to a slow simmer.
Add mushrooms, sliced onion and green pepper.
Cover and stir occasionally.
Let cook about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: dried peach custard
directions: Line
pan
with pastry.
Put in peaches.
Beat together until light.
Pour
over peaches.
Bake at 450° until crust is brown, then lower heat until done.
Use egg whites for top.

title: grape leaf pickles
directions: Wash pickles.
Place in 1 quart jar; cover with boiling vinegar mixture and seal.
Good after 9 days.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix together buttermilk and soda.
Blend sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate (or cocoa) and butter or margarine together. Cool slightly and add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Beat until smooth and pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on lettuce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese with Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill!
Shape into ball or log.
Roll in chopped or ground pecans.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: sour milk cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt and egg.
Alternate sour milk with dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown on top and toothpick comes out clean.
This cake is good with powdered sugar on top, or a Lazy Daisy topping, or any frosting.

title: cherry shortbread
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl and add just enough cherry juice to mix and form into rolls of dough.
Wrap rolls of dough in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice each roll into slices 1/4-inch thick.
Place slices on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
For an extra touch, roll the dough in nuts or in red sugar before chilling.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Pat rolls to form a pastry base in pizza pan. Top with sausage, hash browns and Cheddar cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together. Gently pour over crust. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 20 to 24 minutes at 375°. Cut into wedges to serve. Yields 4 servings.

title: swedish tea rings
directions: Roll in balls and dip each in white of egg; roll in nuts. Bake 5 minutes.
Take thimble and put hole in each.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Fill with frosting or jam.
Makes 14.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and milk.
Add flour and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Good for cupcakes, upside-down cake and plain cake.)

title: broccoli - rice casserole
directions: Place ingredients in large casserole and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove; stir and return to oven for 40 more minutes.

title: easy as pie
directions: Combine apples, water, spices and butter.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in jello, then pudding.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: perfect white bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine yeast and 2 1/2 cups flour.

Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt, stirring constantly, to almost melt shortening. Add to dry mixture in bowl. Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly. Beat 3 minutes at high speed. By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough. Turn out onto lightly floured surface. Knead until smooth and satiny (8 to 10 minutes). Shape into ball. Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 75 minutes.

title: pizza popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Melt butter; add seasonings. Pour over popped popcorn in shallow baking pan; stir to mix well. Heat in preheated oven and stir occasionally. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and mandarin oranges (with juice).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: streusel banana muffins
directions: For streusel, mix brown sugar, 1/4 c. chopped nuts and cinnamon; set aside.
In separate bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and 1/3 c. chopped nuts; set aside.
In third bowl, beat bananas, oil, milk, egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture all at once, stirring with spoon, until flour is just moistened. Batter will be lumpy.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups. Sprinkle with streusel mix.
Bake at 400 degrees approximately 15 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove immediately and cool.

title: olive deviled eggs
directions: Day before serving or early in day, cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks to small mixing bowl; mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill whites with yolk mixture, cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving place eggs on lettuce lined platter.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Slice garlic into large shallow pan.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until blended.
Place steak in pan and pour sauce over it.
Let stand at least 3 hours or overnight.
Grill.

title: pilgrim stuffing
directions: Beat cream, egg yolks and saffron, stirring constantly with a fork.
Stir in spices and salt. Add the bread crumbs.
Mix well. Stir in the raisins or currants. Bake.

title: super-duper french toast(brunch)
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over bread slices laid out flat in large pan.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Cook in butter on grill and serve with powdered sugar or syrup.

title: crawfish bisque
directions: Combine minced vegetables and brown well in enough cooking oil to barely cover.
Pour off excess oil when vegetables are browned. Grind crawfish tails.
Soak bread in water and wring out water.

title: easy no knead yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in barely warm water and set aside.
Cream next 3 ingredients with a fork.
Add egg and cream again.
Add dissolved yeast to this mixture.
Then add flour and mix until all blended.
Pat in a small ball in the mixing bowl.
Put a little oil on the mixing bowl sides and turn dough to coat.
Put a cloth over bowl and let rise to double thickness (about 2 hours).

title: danish pastry with cream puff topping
directions: Cut butter into flour as for pie crust.
Add water to make a soft dough.
Divide into 2 strips 12/2 on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating very well after each egg is added.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan that has been greased.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
I use this to make mini muffins, also.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft. In a large mixing bowl, combine sweet potatoes, sugar cinnamon, nutmeg, a pinch of salt, one-half teaspoons vanilla extract, lemon flavoring, and eggs. Slowly add can of evaporated milk and regular milk and mix well. Pour into pastry-lined pie pan. Cover edge of pie crust with foil. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Remove foil and bake for 20-25 minutes until knife comes out clean. Serve with whipped cream.

title: lemon-lime refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve gelatins in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water; set aside.
Mix and bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool 20 to 25 minutes.
Poke deep holes about 1 inch apart in cake (still in pan) with a meat fork.
Pour gelatin mixture into holes.
Refrigerate cake.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Put apple pie filling in greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top (dry), then sprinkle pecans.
Cut stick of butter and place evenly over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pull-apart parmesan garlic bubble loaf
directions: Cut dough in 16 equal pieces.
Shape in balls.
Place on floured surface; cover.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Stir Parmesan and garlic powder into melted butter, using spoon.
Roll balls in butter mixture.

title: butter rice krispies cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs one at a time until mixture is fluffy.
Add vanilla, then add flour mixture.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into bowl of Rice Krispies.
Place ball on ungreased cookie sheet and press lightly.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put above ingredients, one at a time, into a blender on low speed.
Mix.
Then pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place apples in a small pan; sprinkle with vanilla.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Take pie crust and roll it out.
Cut in stripes and line casserole around edge.
Mix peaches with 3/4 cup of sugar, tapioca and apple pie spice.
Put in lined casserole.
Put few specks margarine on top.
Put leftover crust on top.
Bake at 350° until well cooked, 1 hour.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter.
Mix other ingredients. Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir once after 30 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions; drain. Rinse with cold water; drain.
Set aside.
Combine sour cream and next 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Combine noodles, sour cream mixture, seafood mix and next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Chill 8 hours.
Arrange on lettuce-lined plates.
Garnish, if desired. Garnish: tomato wedges, parsley sprigs.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes, guacamole and shredded lettuce.

title: frying pan shrimp scampi
directions: De-shell shrimp and butterfly.
Dry thoroughly.
Heat ingredients in frying pan and when very hot, add shrimp.
Stir constantly, cooking for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Serve with French roll and wine.

title: wild rice and chicken bake
directions: Place uncooked rice and half of the flavor packet (about 1 1/2 tablespoons) in a 3-quart rectangular baking dish.
Stir in water, soup, water chestnuts, frozen peas and carrot.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika and pepper.
tags: quick-cooking long grain and wild rice

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Bring to boil the margarine, sugar and corn syrup; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popcorn and pour mixture on two greased cookies sheets.
Bake for 1 hour, turning corn by stirring every 15 minutes.
Place in brown paper bag and break apart when cool.

title: wilma's rice
directions: Combine ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious with pork chops.

title: lazy peach pie
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine in oblong cake pan.
Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix 3/4 cup milk with dry ingredients.
Pour over melted butter in cake pan.

title: layered tacos
directions: Layer in order on tray.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: guava jello
directions: Boil 2 cups of water.
Add sugar to boiling water and stir until sugar dissolves; add jello.
In another bowl, melt gelatine in 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour jello mixture into gelatine mixture and add guava juice.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Cut and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake in baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Slowly beat in oil.
Gradually add flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon that have already been mixed together.
Mix in carrots and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken frangelica
directions: Saute chicken breasts.
Add Frangelica and brandy.
Slowly stir in cream.
Add mushrooms and shallots.
Simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Rice pilaf makes a nice accompaniment to this dish. Also, stir-fried, julienned, fresh vegetables.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: This was made in the bread tray like regular biscuits, but a regular bowl may be used.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with meat.

title: microwave rice
directions: Combine rice and water in Pyrex bowl. Cover.
Microwave 5 minutes
on
High.
Reduce
to
medium heat and microwave 13 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes.

title: baked pears and cranberries
directions: Put all ingredients in a small baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve.

title: aunt dianne's beef stroganoff
directions: Heat margarine in large skillet over moderately high heat. Add meat and onion; cook until meat is brown and onion is tender. Remove from heat.
Add soup, sour cream and water.
Stir and place over moderately low heat for about an hour, or until meat is fork-tender.
Serve over cooked, lightly buttered noodles or rice.

title: lemon tamari salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Makes 1 quart.
Will keep in refrigerator about 4 weeks.

title: tossed broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, bacon, onion & cheese.
In a separate bowl, combine all dressing ingredients.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Drain all fruit. Reserve pineapple juice. Mix pudding, pineapple juice and rum flavoring. Mix in fruits and chill. Add bananas at serving time.

title: deep dish salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in serving bowl in order, beginning with lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise over top layer; sprinkle with cheese.
Do not stir!
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Forty-five minutes before serving, remove from refrigerator and garnish with sliced eggs, bacon and tomatoes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the sour cream and vanilla. Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture. Chill dough 1 hour. Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: buckeyes
directions: Work together the first four ingredients with hands. Roll into 1/2 inch balls. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Put a toothpick into ball and dip into melted chocolate. Leave top open so it looks like a buckeye.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly (do not beat).
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Let cool in pan.

title: original coney island sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan.
Simmer until done (thick, about 2 1/2 hours).
Put on hot dogs with mustard and onions.

title: potato delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt margarine.
Mix all other ingredients, except 1/2 cup potato chips. Pour into melted margarine.
Put remaining chips on top.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Place beans in a large saucepan.
Add enough water to cover; bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook on medium-low for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crispy.
Place bacon on paper towels, reserving drippings in the skillet to be used later; crumble bacon.
Add bacon, corn, sausage and onions to beans in saucepan.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 1 hour.
Stir flour into reserved bacon drippings in skillet.
Cook on medium-low heat until bubbly, stirring frequently.
Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups water until mixture boils and thickens, stirring frequently.
Add to soup; simmer 30 minutes.
Season to taste with pepper.
Makes 6 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: funnel cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix egg and milk together.
Add dry ingredients, beat until smooth.
Hold finger over bottom of funnel.
Pour in some batter.
Remove finger and let batter drip in a spiral motion in pan filled with 1-inch of hot oil, 375 degrees. Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Remove from pan and drain on a paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain the salmon, removing all the skin and bones.
Flake the salmon, then combine with the next 6 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly; chill several hours.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Divide dough into 5 parts and pat into 5 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread Apple Filling on warm layers; stack layers.
Makes one 5 layer cake.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan (baking dish).
Sprinkle rice over soup mix.
Dilute mushroom soup with 1 1/2 cans of water.
Pour over rice and soup mix.
Stir and place chicken pieces over rice-soup mixture.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cinnamon rolls(makes 150)
directions: In mixer soften yeast in water, let stand 10 minutes.
Next, add sugar through dry milk then add eggs and flour.
Mix for 10 minutes.
Take out of mixer and split into two batches.
Take one batch and roll into rectangle as long as table and as wide, (if possible without tearing dough).
Then put brown sugar and cinnamon onto dough that has been rubbed with butter or oleo. Next add raisin and nuts and roll as tight as needed.
Cut and place cut side down on cookie sheets lined with baking paper.
Set aside and let dough rise.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: red and yellow salmon berry jam
directions: Wash and bring 3-quart berries.
Measure sugar into a dry dish.
Measure 6 cups of berries into a large kettle.
Add pectin and stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Add measured sugar and mix well. Continue stirring and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil exactly 4 minutes and pour into prepared jars.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Pour milk and soup over croutons, then mix with other ingredients.
Include half of the cheese in the mix and top the mixture with the other half.
Cook at 350° until set in the center.
Cool slightly and cut in squares to serve.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in sugar and vanilla. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill until set.
Top with pie filling.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: kim's quickie meat pie
directions: 1. Pretend the ground round is pie dough. Place it in the bottom and sides of large pie plate as if your baking a
pie. 2. Pour stewed tomatoes in middle (like pie filling).
3. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. Pull out at 15 minutes.
4. Grate cheese on top.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Increase heat to 375° and bake for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, syrup, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Top with pecans. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until set.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: squash bread (cornbread)
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Use Pam spray on a cast iron skillet.
Preheat oven to 400°. Pour your mixture into skillet and cook in oven for about 1 hour.
It will be the best cornbread you have ever eaten.
Be sure and bless the food.
Enjoy.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk; cook over low heat until rice is tender (approximately 40 minutes).
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Spoon egg mixture slowly into rice mixture and return to heat.
When it looks as if it will boil, remove and top with cinnamon.

title: apple butter(make in crock-pot)
directions: Core and chop apples (do not peel).
Combine apples and cider in slow cooking crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or until apples are mushy.
Puree in food processor.
Return mixture to crock-pot.
Add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake and cool chocolate cake.
Cut cake into squares and slice squares in half.
Prepare chocolate mousse following the package directions.
Chop Heath bars into small squares and layer the ingredients in a pan or large bowl in this order:
cake, mousse, Heath bars, walnuts and Cool Whip.	Repeat layers until ingredients are used.

title: baked ziti
directions: In a large pan, brown sausage.
Slice into coin size pieces. Remove from pan and drain.
Melt margarine and cook mushrooms, green pepper and onions until tender (but do not brown).
Blend flour into vegetable mixture.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until it begins to boil. Blend in cheese until melted.
Cook ziti; drain.
Stir hot ziti, cheese, vegetables and sausage together.
Pour into 2-quart buttered dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix, chips, milk and eggs.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured 12-cup tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan. Sift powdered sugar over cake for decoration.

title: curried crab dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, curry, garlic and onion.
Fold in crabmeat.
Garnish with bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly, 15 to 20 minutes, at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Combine butter, shortening, eggs and egg yolks.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Put dry ingredients into brownie pan.
Top with egg white and the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add chocolate chips on top and nuts.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Place 1/2 cup Southwestern Seasoning in a large Ziploc heavy-duty plastic bag.
Lightly beat egg white in a shallow dish; dip chicken into egg white, turning to coat.
Add chicken to bag; seal bag and shake to coat.
Place chicken on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly-roll pan coated with cooking spray.
Lightly coat chicken with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done. Yields 4 servings.

title: western baked beans
directions: Saute onion in oil in small pan or skillet until tender; stir in barbecue sauce, orange, peel and brown sugar.
Combine onion mixture and beans in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; blend well. Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir in orange pieces.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle bacon "bits" over top, if desired, before serving.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool 20 to 25 minutes before inverting on plate. This makes a very moist cake.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Soak biscuit crumbs in water.
When soft, pour off excess water.
Add eggs, cinnamon, cloves, 1 cup milk and sugar.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip meringue bars
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and eggs.
Stir by hand until well combined.
Press in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare frosting with boiling water as directed on package. Spread on chocolate base.
Keep frosting about 2-inches from pan edge. Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream-style corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop in pan with a little grease like pancakes.
Brown on both sides.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add sugar, salt, lemon juice and rind.
Congeal slightly.
Whip Milnot and fold into jello mixture. Cover bottom of glass baking dish with vanilla wafers; fill with jello mixture and cover with wafers.
Chill.

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: Cut 6 tortillas into 1/2 inch strips; set aside.
Cut other 6 into triangles and fry in hot oil until crisp; set aside.
Saute onions and garlic in oil in a Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and paprika.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add tortilla strips and cheese; simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with reserved tortilla fried chips.
Yields 8 cups.

title: ham and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Put a third of the potatoes into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half of the flour-salt mixture.
Add half the ham.
Cover with half the flour mixture.
Add half the ham.
Cover with second third of potatoes, then remaining ham, then rest of potatoes.
Sprinkle on rest of flour mixture.
Dot with margarine; pour milk over all. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and brown on top.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and chill. Roll into balls, chill again.

title: apple cider tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pot.
Bring to a simmer. Wonderful for those winter nights.

title: pork and green chili casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute pork in oil until no pink remains; drain.
Add the beans, soup, tomatoes, chilies, rice, water, salsa and cumin; cook and stir until bubbly.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheese; let stand a few minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Beat in sugar; add oil slowly.
Add vanilla. Sift flour and dry ingredients; add egg mixture, nuts and zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes two 9 x 5-inch loaves or you may use 4 small pans and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ham and swiss rolls
directions: Place slice of Swiss cheese on top of ham slice; roll and secure with toothpick.
Roll in flour, then in beaten egg; coat with flavored bread crumbs and oregano.
Saute in hot oil approximately 5 minutes each side.
May be served with mushroom sauce, mashed potatoes and/or green veggie.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in bottom of lightly greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan to form a crust.
Brown sausage and drain fat.
Put sausage on crust and layer with hash browns.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Cheddar cheese.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over all.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix well; press evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Add to cereal and peanuts.
Spread on large cookie sheet and refrigerate until cold.
Cut into squares and cover with Chocolate Icing.

title: italian chicken
directions: Pour tomato sauce into crock-pot and add all spices.
Cook on high for 2 hours.
Cook chicken in olive oil on high 5 minutes on both sides.
Pour 1/2 cup of tomato sauce in a baking dish.
Keep layering with tomato sauce, chicken and cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave mexican manicotti
directions: Combine ground beef, refried beans, oregano and cumin; mix well.
Fill uncooked manicotti shells with meat mixture.
Arrange in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine water and picante sauce; pour over manicotti shells.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microcook in a countertop microwave oven on High for 10 minutes, giving dish a half turn once.
Using tongs, turn shells over.
Microcook, covered, on Medium for 17 to 19 minutes or until pasta is tender, giving dish a half turn once.
Combine sour cream, green onion and olives.
Spoon down center of casserole; top with cheese.
Microcook, uncovered, on High 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat 1 inch of water to boiling; add broccoli.
Cover and cook until almost tender, about 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and green pepper in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate. Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let stand until cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, cooled date mixture, flour and nutmeats. Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in large plastic dishpan.
Salt lightly.
Cover with ice and let stand for 2 hours.
Rinse and dry on big towels. Pack cucumbers in jars and pour the mixture of sugar, vinegar and spices boiling over them.
Seal.

title: nutty shrimp
directions: Peel, devein and butterfly 1 pound large shrimp.
Combine 1/2 cup all-purpose flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a large plastic bag.
Add shrimp and shake to coat.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sliced almonds in a jelly roll pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients .
Pour into an uncooked 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm.

title: lottie's chocolate cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar, add eggs and salt.
Pour boiling water over cocoa.
Mix together.
Add to egg and sugar mixture. Add vanilla.
Add flour and soda alternately with sour milk.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 minutes.

title: grandma's drippy icing
directions: Combine in a small pan. Stir all of the time while cooking. Boil until thickened, then it is ready to use on cake. Real good on chocolate cake and can be used on other kinds.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Measure all dry ingredients in a small bowl; mix.
In a larger bowl, mix cheese, onion, jalapenos, corn, eggs, oil and milk.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 450° or until brown and firm.

title: canned pear preserves
directions: Put pears in container.
Pour sugar over them and let set overnight.

title: steak and biscuits
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces and season with salt and pepper.
Heat shortening or oil in a large cast-iron skillet. Flour both sides and brown in shortening.
