Add onion to the skillet after turning steaks.
Remove steak and onion from the skillet and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add remaining flour to shortening and cook over low heat until flour begins to brown. Gradually add water, stirring constantly to make a smooth gravy. Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When tender, top with biscuits and brown at 400° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple (including juice) and "dump" it into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle pecans on top. Lightly press pecans into top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine corn bread mix and onion in bowl. Add mayonnaise, cottage cheese, eggs and broccoli; mix well. Pour into 5 x 7 greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian carrots
directions: Prepare onion.
Saute all ingredients, except carrots.
Pour over carrots.
Heat all together.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: ice cream cookie freeze
directions: Place Little Debbie snack cakes in bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan. Spoon ice cream over cookies.
(Wet clean hands for easier spreading.)
Spread Cool Whip over ice cream.
Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips or M&M's on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: tuna cheese chowder
directions: In 3-quart pan, cook carrots and onions in margarine until onion is soft, but not brown.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and broth; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in tuna, celery seed, Worcestershire and salt.
Heat through.
Just before serving, add cheese and stir until melted.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions, drain off fat. Coat with taco seasoning mix. Place in casserole dish. Add rest of ingredients in any order. Bake 40 minutes at 400 degrees or until bubbly.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk by stirring.
Add lemon juice and a little rind and pineapple. Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze. May be frozen in refrigerator, if so, stir several times while freezing.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: In small bowl, mix together soy sauce, sherry, sugar, ginger and garlic powder.
Stir in meat and let marinate for 10 minutes. Broil 4 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes each side or until done as desired.
Serve on rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brown stone front cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen daiquiries
directions: *Use empty limeade can.

title: sausage balls
directions: Place cooked and crumbled sausage and both cheeses in microwave-safe dish and microwave until cheeses are melted.
Stir in Bisquick.

title: old fashioned potato candy
directions: Cook potato with jacket on. Peel and mash very fine. Add sugar, enough to make a very stiff dough. Roll mixture out and spread with creamy peanut butter. Roll up like a jelly roll. Cool in the refrigerator. Slice to serve.

title: our favorite barbecue hash
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cook stew beef and pork until well done (meat will be stringy; add water as needed).
Combine beef, pork and chicken in large open pot.
Add sauces, onion and ground beef; stir constantly, simmering very slowly, for about 1 hour. Add extra sauce or water, if needed, to keep hash from sticking.

title: peach tree fuzzy navel cake
directions: Puree the undrained peaches and combine with Schnapps, sugar and orange juice. Store in covered container for 24 hours. Do not stir again.

title: good and glossy cookie frosting
directions: Combine water and corn syrup in heavy saucepan. Add sugar and blend well. Using a candy thermometer, cook over medium-low heat until temperature reaches 100°. Stir constantly! Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Cool for 5 to 8 minutes. Ice cookies. Stir icing occasionally. You can sprinkle on candy decorations, nonpareils and colored sugars before the icing hardens.

title: maple pie
directions: Beat together in pan: milk, syrup and eggs.
Boil on medium for 5 minutes.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Chill.
Cover with whipped cream and toasted coconut.
(Toast coconut in oven with small amount of margarine.)

title: dream cake
directions: *Do not whip:
use right from envelope.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve with raw veggies or chips.

title: granola
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients until well blended.
Mix honey, milk and oil.
Pour over dry ingredients; stir well.
Spread on baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir often. Cool. Store in sandwich bags.

title: easy vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix together the spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce and water and add to meat.
Beat the eggs, then add milk, vegetable oil, flour, salt and Parmesan cheese.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Add meat and sauce mixture.
Pour batter over meat.
Sprinkle
on Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Let cool about 5 minutes.

title: ruby red salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: lo-cal chicken soup
directions: Deskin and bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Cook tomatoes, garlic and water 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until reduced by half.
Add chicken, peas and spices and other vegetables.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Yield:
15 cups, 95 calories per cup. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chex mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Slowly melt butter in long shallow pan. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add Chex and nuts, mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool. Yields 6 3/4 cups.

title: con's cucumbers
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers.
Put in bowl and add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Soak for 1/2 hour, then add peppers, onions, celery and mustard seed.

title: turkey meat loaf(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in lightly greased 4 x 8 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan or shape in loaf form and place in lightly greased baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until meat is no longer pink in center.
Special from "Heart Beat".

title: ham, corn and potato chowder
directions: Recipe may be halved or doubled.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake ingredients.
Beat for about 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake for 40 or 45 minutes, or until done, at 350°.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in a jar.
Add two heaping teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate, butter and peanut butter.
Pour over Crispix.
Pour powdered sugar over top and mix together.
Bon appetit!

title: 24-hour oriental salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl and toss lightly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix. Pour on top. Cook for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hal williams tasty turkey spaghetti sauce
directions: Note:
May substitute hot Italian sausage for the sweet turkey, also recipe serves small army instead of six.

title: crimson banana delight
directions: Place unopened raspberries in large bowl.
Add hot tap water to cover; set aside to thaw.
Drain thawed raspberries, reserving 1/4 cup of the syrup (reserve remaining syrup for another use).
Peel bananas; cut diagonally into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange on four individual dessert plates in sunburst pattern.
Brush or drizzle with 2 teaspoons of the lemon juice.

title: chops milanaise
directions: Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in a shallow bowl.
Dip chops in flour, then in egg, and dredge in bread crumb mixture. Melt butter in large skillet and brown chops.
Reduce heat, cover and cook for about 3 minutes.
Remove cover and continue cooking until chops are completely cooked.
Season with salt and pepper. Serve with lemon and buttered noodles.

title: great western beans
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Cook hamburger until brown.
Add all at once the onion soup mix, water, catsup, mustard, vinegar and pork and beans.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers.
Put 1 layer in bottom of punch bowl. Break the layer up into pieces.
Pour crushed pineapple with juice over the cake.
Prepare the vanilla pudding according to package directions.
Pour half over cake and pineapple.
Place second cake layer, which is broken into pieces also, over the pudding.
Put thawed strawberries, with the juice, over the cake.
Pour rest of vanilla pudding over the strawberries and cover with Dream Whip or Cool Whip topping.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving. Use a really large spoon for serving so you can dig deep into the bowl!
Delicious!

title: old fashion applesauce cake(grandmother booth's)
directions: Mix
ingredients well, plus juice of cherries, plus 1/2 cup liquor
(mix nuts, cherries and raisins with 1/2 cup flour you saved and add to
cake
mixture
last).
Bake
at 325° for 1 3/4 hours or until brown or clean to a tester.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs, corn and milk; mix well.
Pour into dish and dot with butter.
Bake for 1 hour.
Center should be almost firm.

title: sauce for roast duck
directions: In saucepan over low heat, cook wine, peppers, bay leaf, thyme and onion until reduced to 2 tablespoons.
Blend butter with flour; stir into wine mixture until melted and mixed.
Strain through fine sieve.
Briskly stir all juices from carved duck into sauce and add sour cream.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in a large skillet. Drain.
Add garlic powder, tomato sauce, corn, olives, salt and chili powder. Slowly add cheese to melt.
Pour into greased 11-inch pie plate. Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions. Spread over meat mixture. Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tennessee chili
directions: Brown
ground
beef,
stirring	constantly in saucepan. Add onions, tomatoes and bell peppers.	Cook until soft, then add beans, chili powder and garlic powder.
Mix well, then add the vinegar.
The vinegar is what gives this chili its special tangy taste.
Stir
it occasionally, while relaxing with your guest. After
an hour, just serve it up with a freshly tossed salad and crackers.

title: red pepper jelly for meat
directions: Boil peppers, sugar and vinegar for 6 to 10 minutes.
Add Certo; boil 3 minutes.
Pour into glasses and seal.

title: buster bar parfait
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add crushed Oreos, reserving 3/4 cup for top of dessert.
Mix and pat gently for bottom crust. Add softened vanilla ice cream.
Smooth over crust; freeze.
Cover ice cream layer with fudge sauce.
Then sprinkle peanuts.
Spread Cool Whip over peanuts.
Sprinkle with reserved Oreo cookie crumbs.
Freeze.
Thaw for 20 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal macaroons
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl and blend well.
In large bowl, cream butter, sugar and eggs; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Then drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: lone star caviar
directions: Cover peas with water and soak at least 6 hours.
Drain well. Put in saucepan and add water to cover. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and allow to simmer until tender (about 45 minutes). Drain well. Blend in dressing and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Makes 7 1/2 cups.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut buns in 4 strips (long ways).
Melt oleo.
Stir in spices. Spread on bread strips.
Bake on cookie sheet for 1 hour at 300°. Good with salad or spaghetti.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Stir together bran cereal and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Add apples, egg and oil, beating until blended.
Add flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Do not over mix.
Fill greased 2 1/2 x 1 1/4 inch muffin pan cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until done. Makes 12 muffins.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Note:
Can add other ingredients: raisins, chocolate chips, etc.

title: impossible pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on bottom of pie plate. Combine packed brown sugar, milk, corn syrup, biscuit baking mix, softened butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix for 1 minute.
Pour in plate. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: praline 'n cream pies
directions: Brown nuts and coconut in margarine to make praline mixture; set aside to cool.
Mix softened cream cheese with sweetened condensed milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pie shell, then add 1/4 praline mixture.
Drizzle on 1/4 jar of topping.
Repeat layers, ending with cream cheese mixture topped with drizzle of butterscotch topping.

title: baked squash
directions: Cube and cook squash until tender; drain and mash. Add beaten egg, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, onion, margarine, sugar, salt and pepper to taste. Mix well and pour into a greased 7 x 11-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender; drain and mash. Measure 1 cup squash.
Combine with egg; stir well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add squash and onion; stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil; turn once when golden.

title: taco soup
directions: Crumble, brown and drain hamburger. Add onions; cook until opaque.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix well before adding tomatoes, corn and beans.
If there is not enough liquid for your soup, add tomato juice or tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve. Better leftover, flavors blended.

title: kay's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
If mixture is still thin, bake just a few more minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, cream of tartar and salt. Add the Crisco and buttermilk. Mix together and empty onto well floured board. Roll out to approximately 1/2-inch thickness. Bake in hot oven at 400° approximately 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust to hold in filling.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes and top with Cheddar cheese. Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Blend sugar and oil; add eggs.
Fold in dry ingredients and mix well.
Add drained pineapple and carrots and mix.
Fold in walnuts or pecans.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix ingredients; form into rolls.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Place softened butter in bowl. Add peanut butter, sugar, vanilla and milk. Mix with electric mixer 2 to 3 minutes. If too thin add sugar, if too thick add milk.

title: reuben dip
directions: Cut corned beef into small pieces. Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes until it bubbles. Keep warm in a crock-pot. Serve with rye or pumpernickel bread.

title: healthy fruit juice cocktail
directions: Mix and drink 2 ounces each day the rest of your life!

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; pour off excess fat.
Add bell pepper, onion and one cup celery to sausage and saute.
Set aside.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon in thirds.
Wrap bacon around water chestnuts and secure with toothpicks.
Put on ungreased shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Drain.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over chestnuts.
Return to oven (350°) for 10 minutes.

title: debbie's cheese ball
directions: Mix
ingredients
together.
This
is
easiest if cream cheese is room temperature or microwaved for approximately 45 seconds. Chill, then serve on crackers or with veggies.

title: lacy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together thoroughly.
Add vanilla, egg and blend in salt and oats.
Chill several hours in refrigerator. Make small balls and place far apart on aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until brown.
Slide foil onto rack and let cool.
Cookies will then peel from foil.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Butter 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle
bottom
with a layer of cracker crumbs, then a
layer
of oysters.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Arrange in alternate layers with top layer being crackers.
Pour over the
oyster
liquor and milk.	Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a bowl. Mix in another bowl the remaining 4 ingredients. Pour over vegetables. Toss and refrigerate. Drain before serving.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Make pound cake according to directions.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake according to box directions.
When complete, spread peanut butter over cake.
Place in oven approximately 3 minutes (until peanut butter is slightly melted).
Then pour chocolate chips over cake and spread evenly.
(For easier spreading, place cake in oven until chips are softened.)
Freeze around 2 hours.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: In greased casserole, layer vegetables and rice in order given.
Combine seasoning and tomato sauce; pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Good!

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a large mixing bowl; set aside.
Cream shortening gradually adding 1 cup sugar; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix until well blended.

title: party mints
directions: Mix thoroughly with hands.
Dust molds (rubber) with granulated sugar.
Press mixture into mold and turn out.

title: that broccoli stuff
directions: *Any type of salt crackers work.
I use about 1 package of saltines for a large batch (crumble fine).

title: good good cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or loaf pans. While cake is baking, mix 1/2 box powdered sugar and lemon or orange juice to make thin icing.
When cake tests done, take a meat fork and punch holes in cake.
Pour icing mixture over cake for topping.

title: foil chicken
directions: Rinse
and
dry
chicken.
Put	onion
slices
on foil. Season chicken
and
put
on top of onions.
Chicken should be skin side up.
Make
sure
chicken
is
in a single layer and there is onion under all the chicken.
Put vegetables to taste in packet.	Seal the packet, place on a bed of coals and cook for 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook water, syrup and sugar to 270°.
Add raw peanuts and cook to 315°, stirring constantly so peanuts won't burn.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Stir until butter is melted; add salt and soda.
Stir briskly until foaming peak is reached.
Pour quickly into large, buttered pans; let cool.
Break into pieces. Store in an airtight container in a cool, dry place.

title: tropical punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid packages and sugar in water with ice.
Add soda, the juices and ginger ale.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, broth and rice and put in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Season chicken with salt, pepper, paprika and garlic salt.
Place on top of rice mixture.
Melt butter and add lemon juice and sugar.
Pour on top of chicken and rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Mix in margarine as for pie crust.
Take out one cup of this mixture for topping.
To remainder, add the eggs, milk and vanilla. Blend well and spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread fruit filling gently over batter and top with reserved crumbs.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Combine sugar, water and red cinnamon drops in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook about 3 minutes in Radarange oven.
Core and pare apples.
Stick 3 or 4 cloves into each apple.
Place apples in the red cinnamon syrup.
Cook about 7 to 8 minutes or until apples are tender but firm.
Turn apples every 2 1/2 minutes.
Cool apples in syrup before serving.

title: salt risin' bread(makes two 8-inch loaves)
directions: On the day before you undertake this operation, you must start the starter.
So peel and finely chop the potato.
Place in medium bowl and stir in the boiling water, cornmeal, sugar and salt. Cover and set aside overnight at room temperature.

title: aleasha's love cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into little balls and share with someone you love.

title: nanny-grammy's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Bring butter, cream cheese and eggs to room temperature, about 1 hour. Grease and flour 9-inch fluted tube pan. Set aside.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix and put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 40 minutes or longer at 350°; watch.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Spread half of the cornflakes mixed with margarine in bottom of greased casserole.
Spread cabbage and onions over crumbs.
Mix milk, soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and pour over cabbage. Spread cheese over soup mixture.
Spread with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: apricot glazed ham
directions: Soak the ham overnight in enough water to cover it. Refrigerate.
(This removes excess salt.)

title: pecan balls
directions: Work butter and vanilla into other ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 300° for 8 minutes.
Roll in 4x sugar.

title: yellow split pea soup
directions: Place ingredients in a large pot.
Cover with water (about 6 to 8 cups).
Cook on low heat several hours, being sure to add water if necessary.

title: surprise casserole
directions: Season hamburger with salt and pepper. Shape into bite-sized meatballs around cubes of cheese. Saute meatballs in skillet until brown on all sides; drain. Cook noodles using package directions. Place in lightly greased casserole. Stir in soups, Parmesan cheese and meatballs. Top with bread crumbs. Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Save half of dressing for top.
Cook squash, onion and carrots until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into casserole dish; sprinkle top with dressing.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles.

title: hidden valley ranch sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper.

title: buttered pecans
directions: Place pecans in microwave dish.
Place in center of oven. Cook on medium to high for 3 minutes, stirring once.
Pour in bowl and add butter.
Stir.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in large pan.
Put on stove and bring to a boil.
Boil for 9 minutes.
Stir at all times.
Take off stove and add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Stir well; add nuts.
Pour in a large buttered cookie sheet.
Cut when cool.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef, drain. Mix in 1/2 jar picante sauce.
On each tortilla, spread refried beans, a tbsp. of meat mixture, and a small amount of cheese.
Roll up each tortilla and place in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread remaining picante sauce over tortillas and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly around edges.

title: baked coon
directions: The
raccoon
which
makes
free with the farmer's corn gets very fat in the fall, on the corn, apples and clover and makes delicious
eating.	Though often thrown away because of the prejudice that many people have against wild meat.	First skin the
coon carefully, then remove the layer of fat, which is
often an
inch
thick and right under the skin.	This fat would	give the
meat a disagreeable, oily taste, if left on. But it is nice and white and can be tried out the same as leaf lard, and used for soap.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook noodles as
directed.
Drain.
Heat
margarine and cream over low heat.
Stir
in
cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over hot noodles.
Toss to coat.
Sprinkle with parsley. Great with scallops or shrimp added.

title: springtime punch
directions: Pour Hawaiian Punch into a punch bowl.
Add sherbet.
Pour ginger ale over the sherbet.
Add ice and champagne, if desired.

title: lucky if you get a piece
directions: Melt butter; add flour and nuts.
Mix well in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Bake at 250° about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Add strawberries and bananas together and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Then spread strawberry glaze on top of that.
Sprinkle with crushed pecans and chill.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Stir crushed strawberries and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Let stand 15 minutes.
Re-stir.
Add Certo.
Put into pint containers.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Freeze.

title: super quick salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with dry Jell-O.
Add whipped topping and your favorite fruit.
Good combinations are orange Jell-O with mandarin oranges, peaches or pineapple and strawberry Jell-O with fruit cocktail.

title: broccoli cheese potato bake
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and hot pepper sauce.
Add potatoes and onions.
Toss to coat.
Put into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, arranging potato mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: cheesy green bean casserole(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Cook bacon. Reserve 1/4 cup drippings. Cook beans 10 minutes with drippings; drain. Add pepper and onions to beans. Mix lightly. Add mushrooms. Spoon into serving dish.
Microwave cheese spread; pour over beans. Sprinkle with bacon and bake at 350°.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix the Dream Whip as usual; beat until fluffy.
Cream together the powdered sugar, eggs and soft butter.
Fold the pineapple and nut meats in gently with first mixture.
Grease the dish; sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, top and bottom. Refrigerate; ready to eat.

title: lobster tails on the grill
directions: Cut bottom of lobster to the shell, but not all the way through.
Cut all membrane from under lobster and discard.
Break shell so lobster can butterfly, but not completely in half.
Brush lobster with butter and place on grill, meat side down, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn lobster over; brush again with butter and season with garlic salt or preferred seasonings.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes, shell side down, or until done, depending on size and heat of grill.
Lobster is cooked when meat turns opaque.

title: french toast
directions: In a mixing bowl, put eggs, sugar, salt and milk.
Mix together thoroughly.
Dip bread slices in batter.
Fry on lightly greased medium hot pan.
Brown on both sides.
Serve sprinkled with icing sugar and fresh strawberries for a special treat.

title: roast beef with vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and place beef roast in medium size Reynolds oven bag, using instructions with bag.
Bake for 1 hour.
Peel and cube potatoes and carrots; peel and slice onion. Cut off tips of celery and cube.
Open cooking bag and place potatoes, carrots, onion and celery in bag.
Reseal and bake for an additional hour.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour 1/4 cup teriyaki sauce over chicken and put in oven.
Check often and turn over several times to keep from drying out.
Slice onions and bell peppers and put in preheated skillet with oil.
Stir-fry vegetables until tender.
Remove from heat.
When chicken is done, serve chicken smothered with vegetables.
May serve with rice.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Combine sauteed mixture with shredded, cooked chicken, chicken soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Pour in prepared 10 x 15-inch pan.
Top with Swiss cheese, crescent rolls, melted margarine and almonds.
Bake at 375° until heated through and crescent rolls are brown.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix sauce; pour it over carrots while hot.
Serve cold.

title: beignets and doughnuts
directions: Pour hot water over Crisco and sugar.
Stir and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and stir in cooled mixture.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Stir in 4 cups of flour and beat.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Place in large bowl that has been oiled.
Brush with melted Crisco.
Cover with damp cloth and chill.
When ready to use, knead lightly with flour and then roll to 1/4-inch and cut in diamond shapes. Fry in hot oil about 3-inches deep.
Drain on towel.
Then shake in bag with powdered sugar.
This also makes good rolls and keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: sweet and sour smoked sausage
directions: Place sausage pieces in crock-pot.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over sausage.
Start crock-pot on high, turn back to low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: party mix
directions: Melt oleo and seasonings.
Pour over corn, etc., mixture and mix well. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients. Stir well, until smooth.
Pour over first set of ingredients and stir lightly until mixed well.
Garnish with hard-cooked eggs.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: In a crock-pot, put stew beef, potatoes, carrots and celery. Stir.
Also add remaining ingredients.
Stir occasionally until all beef is cooked through and potatoes and carrots are easy to cut.
Start crock-pot early in morning to give stew beef plenty of time to cook.

title: lazy day cake
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder. Add milk and beat until smooth.
Pour batter into baking dish.
Spread pineapple over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: mornay sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and cayenne.
Cook for
1 minute.
Remove.
Stir in milk until mixture is smooth. Cook over low heat, stirring until thick.
Add cheese.

title: potato soup
directions: In large soup pan saute bacon, onion and celery until tender. Add cubed potatoes; cover with water and boil until potatoes are tender.
Drain water until it covers potatoes.
Add can of evaporated milk and butter.
Mash potatoes and warm soup.
Serve hot.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Stir together sugar and oil.
Beat in egg.
Add 1 cup sour milk (you can make sour milk by adding 1 tablespoon vinegar with 1 cup sweet milk; let set 5 minutes).
Sift 2 cups flour and baking soda on top of mixture.
Put 1/2 to 2 1/2 cups chopped rhubarb with flour.
Then stir everything together.
pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon to make a coating before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Dissolve butter, syrup and sugar on medium heat.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and mix with sugar.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and cook at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: yams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil or steam yams for 20 minutes or until barely tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel and cut to equal 1 2/3 cups.
In shallow baking dish, place yams; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Soften marmalade and mix with orange juice.
Add sage and salt and pour over yams.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Work in shortening.
Add vinegar and egg.
Add ice water.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine next 4 ingredients in bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, egg and half the flour.
Beat well.
Add enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease surface.
Let rise, covered, in warm place for 1 hour or until doubled.
Divide into halves.
Roll each portion on floured surface to 12-inch circle.
Cut into 12 wedges and roll up from wide end.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Let rise 30 minutes or until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with garlic salt, onion salt and black pepper.
Brown in small amount of oil, then remove and place in baking dish.
Saute the onion and bell pepper in skillet, then add the soups and milk.
Cook these together until mixed into a gravy, then pour over the pork chops and bake for about 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: easy carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots, apples and raisins.
Mix salad dressing and orange juice together and pour over other ingredients.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crumb cake
directions: Put the first three ingredients together like a pie crust. Keep out 3/4 of these ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients. Put into a greased pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk with bread crumbs, sugar, salt and oleo.
Pour some of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Combine with other ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about an hour or until pudding is firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and cut up apples, oranges and bananas.
Add orange juice and pudding; mix well and chill.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Add flour and salt.
Cook until bubbly. Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and smooth. Add 1 cup cheese. Stir until melted.
Add eggs, potatoes, ham and parsley.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or may microwave.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook and drain beans.
In buttered shallow baking dish, distribute 2/3 cup of package stuffing crumbs.
Arrange beans in layer over crumbs, then scatter almonds.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Half of recipe makes 20 muffins.
